00:11:09.120 --> 00:11:10.630
SEBELIUS.

00:11:10.630 --> 00:11:14.070
THE CASE GOT A LOT OF HEADLINES
FOR A COUPLE OF REASONS.

00:11:14.070 --> 00:11:19.270
FIRST AT THE MOST BASIC LEVEL
IT UPHELD THE CONSTITUTIONALITY

00:11:19.270 --> 00:11:21.690
OF THE AFFORDABLE CARE
ACT, OR AS THE PRESS

00:11:21.690 --> 00:11:24.220
LIKES TO CALL IT OBAMACARE.

00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:26.650
THAT WAS A BIG DEAL
IN AND OF ITSELF.

00:11:26.650 --> 00:11:30.230
THE COURT SAYS THAT CONGRESS HAS
THE CONSTITUTIONAL AUTHORITY TO

00:11:30.230 --> 00:11:32.870
ORDER YOU OR ME TO
BUY HEALTH INSURANCE,

00:11:32.870 --> 00:11:36.530
OR PAY A FEE OR
FINE IF WE DON'T.

00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:39.980
CONGRESS HAD NEVER QUITE DONE
ANYTHING LIKE THAT BEFORE,

00:11:39.980 --> 00:11:44.690
SO THE DECISION
ITSELF WAS A BIG DEAL.

00:11:44.690 --> 00:11:50.650
SECOND, THE COURT DIVIDED IN A
KIND OF GOOFY, INTERESTING, AND

00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:52.340
REVEALING WAY.

00:11:52.340 --> 00:11:52.864
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:52.864 --> 00:11:55.280
YOU KNOW, ONE THAT MADE PEOPLE
KIND OF SCRATCH THEIR HEADS

00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:57.780
AND SAY WHAT'S GOING ON.

00:11:57.780 --> 00:12:01.980
CHIEF JUSTICE ROBERTS WAS AT
THE CENTER OF ALL OF THIS.

00:12:01.980 --> 00:12:05.640
IN ONE PART OF HIS
OPINION THE COURT

00:12:05.640 --> 00:12:09.840
SAID THAT THE INDIVIDUAL
MANDATE COULD BE JUSTIFIED

00:12:09.840 --> 00:12:12.720
UNDER CONGRESS' POWER TO TAX.

00:12:12.720 --> 00:12:14.840
UNDER THE CONSTITUTIONAL
TAXING POWER

00:12:14.840 --> 00:12:19.280
EVEN THOUGH CONGRESS HAD
NOT CALLED THE THING A TAX.

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:22.260
THERE CHIEF JUSTICE ROBERTS
WAS JOINED BY THE COURT'S FOUR

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:24.980
DEMOCRATIC APPOINTEES.

00:12:24.980 --> 00:12:28.480
IN ANOTHER PART OF THE CHIEF
JUSTICE'S OPINION HE WROTE THAT

00:12:28.480 --> 00:12:31.950
THE INDIVIDUAL MANDATE COULD
NOT JUSTIFIED AS AN EXERCISE

00:12:31.950 --> 00:12:34.720
OF CONGRESS' POWER TO
QUOTE REGULATE COMMERCE

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:36.420
AMONG THE SEVERAL STATES.

00:12:36.420 --> 00:12:41.210
IN OTHER WORDS OBAMACARE PASSED
MUSTER UNDER THE TAXING CLAUSE

00:12:41.210 --> 00:12:44.340
BUT FLUNKED THE COMMERCE CLAUSE.

00:12:44.340 --> 00:12:47.120
THOUGH NO OTHER JUSTICE
JOINED THE CHIEF'S OPINION

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:49.020
ON THE COMMERCE
CLAUSE, THE COURT'S

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:53.180
FOUR OTHER REPUBLICAN APPOINTEES
WROTE A JOINT DISSENT THAT

00:12:53.180 --> 00:12:57.680
ESSENTIALLY SAID THE SAME
THING AS THE CHIEF JUSTICE DID.

00:12:57.680 --> 00:13:00.180
THIS IS AN ODD TURN OF EVENTS.

00:13:00.180 --> 00:13:03.020
USUALLY IF THE COURT FINDS THAT
CONGRESS HAS THE POWER TO DO

00:13:03.020 --> 00:13:05.960
SOMETHING UNDER ONE CLAUSE
OF THE CONSTITUTION,

00:13:05.960 --> 00:13:11.200
IT DOESN'T BOTHER TO OPINE ON
WHETHER IT HAS THE POWER TO DO

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:14.705
THE SAME THING UNDER ANOTHER
CLAUSE OF THE CONSTITUTION.

00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:21.230
WE CALL THIS A DICTUM.

00:13:21.230 --> 00:13:25.950
AND THE COURT ISN'T SUPPOSED
TO WRITE ON ABSTRACT QUESTIONS

00:13:25.950 --> 00:13:28.630
THAT DON'T AFFECT THE
OUTCOME OF THE DECISION.

00:13:28.630 --> 00:13:31.470
BUT TODAY I'M ACTUALLY GOING
TO TALK ABOUT THE DICTA IN THE

00:13:31.470 --> 00:13:35.120
