FRONT THAT THE CHIEF JUSTICE
AND THE JOINT DISSENT AT LEAST

00:14:16.880 --> 00:14:20.580
PROPORTED TO REST ON THE
TEXT OF THE COMMERCE CLAUSE.

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:21.704
AS YOU MIGHT THINK.

00:14:21.704 --> 00:14:24.120
THEY WANTED TO POINT TO SOME
PART OF THE CONSTITUTION THAT

00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:25.290
WAS AN ISSUE.

00:14:25.290 --> 00:14:28.520
THEY ARGUED BECAUSE THE
INDIVIDUAL MANDATE TOLD PEOPLE

00:14:28.520 --> 00:14:32.120
SITTING AT HOME MINDING THEIR
OWN BUSINESS TO GO OUT AND BUY

00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:35.190
SOMETHING, THAT THERE WAS
SIMPLY NO COMMERCE HERE

00:14:35.190 --> 00:14:37.050
FOR CONGRESS TO REGULATE.

00:14:37.050 --> 00:14:38.910
IN OTHER WORDS,
WHAT THEY SAID WAS

00:14:38.910 --> 00:14:42.630
IN THE STATUTE THAT
CONGRESS CREATED RATHER

00:14:42.630 --> 00:14:47.600
THAN REGULATED COMMERCE, AND
THAT THAT WAS NOT PERMISSIBLE.

00:14:47.600 --> 00:14:50.190
LOOK, THIS IS AN
INGENIOUS ARGUMENT.

00:14:50.190 --> 00:14:51.980
INGENIOUS.

00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:54.140
BUT IT DOESN'T HOLD WATER.

00:14:54.140 --> 00:14:55.410
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:55.410 --> 00:14:58.670
AND HERE'S WHY.

00:14:58.670 --> 00:15:04.430
THE OBAMACARE STATUTE IS ALL
ABOUT INTERSTATE COMMERCE.

00:15:04.430 --> 00:15:07.410
EVEN IF I'M SITTING AT HOME
MINDING MY OWN BUSINESS NOT

00:15:07.410 --> 00:15:10.710
BUYING ANYTHING
MUCH LESS INSURANCE,

00:15:10.710 --> 00:15:14.300
THERE IS A MASSIVE INTERSTATE
HEALTH INSURANCE MARKET

00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:17.000
OPERATING ALL AROUND ME.

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:20.100
AND THE INDIVIDUAL
MANDATE UNQUESTIONABLY

00:15:20.100 --> 00:15:24.430
AND QUITE DIRECTLY REGULATES
THAT INTERSTATE MARKET.

00:15:24.430 --> 00:15:26.110
AND HERE'S HOW.

00:15:26.110 --> 00:15:30.260
A DIFFERENT AND UNCONTESTED
SECTION OF THE ACA SAYS THAT

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:34.670
YOU AND I HAVE THE RIGHT TO GO
OUT AND BUY INSURANCE, EVEN IF

00:15:34.670 --> 00:15:37.040
WE HAVE PREEXISTING CONDITIONS.

00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:38.880
SO IF I'M A HEALTHY
YOUNG PERSON,

00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:42.870
WHY ON EARTH WOULD I BUY
INSURANCE UNTIL I NEEDED IT?

00:15:42.870 --> 00:15:46.740
THAT IS TO SAY UNTIL
I ACTUALLY GOT SICK.

00:15:46.740 --> 00:15:49.590
THIS INCENTIVE THREATENED TO
DRAIN THE HEALTHIEST PEOPLE

00:15:49.590 --> 00:15:52.990
OUT OF THE RISK POO IN THE
INTERSTATE HEALTH INSURANCE

00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:53.940
MARKET.

00:15:53.940 --> 00:15:58.990
AND THE INDIVIDUAL MANDATE
REGULATES THE INTERSTATE

00:15:58.990 --> 00:16:02.090
COMMERCE AND INTERSTATE HEALTH
INSURANCE MARKET BY PUSHING

00:16:02.090 --> 00:16:08.190
THOSE POTENTIAL FREE RIDERS
BACK INTO THE RISK POOL, PLAIN

00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:09.930
AND SIMPLE.

00:16:09.930 --> 00:16:14.480
SO IF IT'S NOT THE TEXT
OF THE COMMERCE CLAUSE

00:16:14.480 --> 00:16:19.700
THAT'S REALLY DOING THE
WORK HERE, WHAT IS IT?

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:23.850
CERTAINLY NO CLAUSE OF THE
CONSTITUTION TELLS CONGRESS

00:16:23.850 --> 00:16:27.010
THAT IT CAN'T MANDATE
INDIVIDUAL BEHAVIOR.

00:16:27.010 --> 00:16:30.330
NOR IS THERE ANY UNSTATED
CONSTITUTIONAL TRADITION OR

00:16:30.330 --> 00:16:34.150
PRACTICE OR LINE OF PRECEDENT
THAT PROHIBITS CONGRESS FROM

00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:38.080
ORDERING PEOPLE TO BUY THINGS
IF DOING SO WOULD HELP CONGRESS

00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:41.210
REGULATE INTERSTATE COMMERCE.

00:16:41.210 --> 00:16:44.510
SO WHAT EXPLAINS THE CHIEF
JUSTICE'S AND THE JOINT

00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:47.710
DISSENT'S POSITION?

00:16:47.710 --> 00:16:49.680
A COUPLE OF THINGS.

00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:53.820
FIRST, AS I MENTIONED, CONGRESS
HAD NEVER DONE ANYTHING QUITE

00:16:53.820 --> 00:16:55.430
LIKE THIS BEFORE.

00:16:55.430 --> 00:17:00.590
FOR THE JUSTICES WHO WERE
SKEPTICAL OF THE COMMERCE POWER

00:17:00.590 --> 00:17:07.319
JUSTIFICATION FOR THE STATUTE,
THE ABSENCE OF A PREEXISTING

00:17:07.319 --> 00:17:10.030
PRACTICE OF, LIKE THE
INDIVIDUAL MANDATE,

00:17:10.030 --> 00:17:12.900
WAS QUOTE THE MOST
TELLING INDICATION

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:17.260
OF A CONSTITUTIONAL ISSUE OR
A CONSTITUTIONAL INFIRMITY.

00:17:17.260 --> 00:17:23.880
SECOND, THE STATUTE
REFLECTED A LARGE EXPANSION

00:17:23.880 --> 00:17:25.859
OF FEDERAL POWER.

00:17:25.859 --> 00:17:29.680
AND THE CHIEF JUSTICE'S WORDS
QUOTE ALLOWING CONGRESS TO

00:17:29.680 --> 00:17:34.760
JUSTIFY FEDERAL REGULATION
BY POINTING TO THE EFFECT OF

00:17:34.760 --> 00:17:38.990
INACTION ON COMMERCE WOULD
BRING COUNTLESS DECISIONS AN

00:17:38.990 --> 00:17:41.440
INDIVIDUAL COULD
POTENTIALLY MAKE WITHIN THE

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:44.880
SCOPE OF FEDERAL
REGULATION AND EMPOWER

00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:49.000
CONGRESS TO MAKE THOSE
DECISIONS FOR HIM.

00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:52.020
TO PUT IT COLLOQUIALLY,
IF CONGRESS CAN

00:17:52.020 --> 00:17:59.050
MAKE US BUY INSURANCE, IT CAN
ALSO MAKE US EAT OUR SPINACH.

00:17:59.050 --> 00:18:01.370
ACTUALLY THE COURT
SAID BROCCOLI.

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:04.990
BUT YOU GET THE IDEA.

00:18:04.990 --> 00:18:09.730
THAT THE CHIEF JUSTICE WROTE IS
NOT THE COUNTRY THE FRAMERS' OF

00:18:09.730 --> 00:18:13.170
OUR CONSTITUTION ENVISIONED.

00:18:13.170 --> 00:18:16.640
AT ONE LEVEL THE CHIEF JUSTICE
IS QUITE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:19.750
THIS IS NOT THE COUNTRY
THE FRAMERS ENVISIONED.

00:18:24.330 --> 00:18:28.350
BUT THAT'S NOT REALLY THE
LEGALLY RELEVANT POINT.

00:18:28.350 --> 00:18:32.040
EVEN FOR ORIGINALISTS.

00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:36.860
THE FRAMERS OBVIOUSLY DIDN'T
ANTICIPATE A COUNTRY OF 320

00:18:36.860 --> 00:18:40.820
MILLION PEOPLE, A GLOBAL
ECONOMY, UBER CARS,

00:18:40.820 --> 00:18:46.730
APPLE WATCHES, OR EVEN AN
INTERSTATE HEALTH INSURANCE

00:18:46.730 --> 00:18:48.360
MARKET.

00:18:48.360 --> 00:18:51.920
WHAT THEY DID
ANTICIPATE WAS THIS.

00:18:51.920 --> 00:18:55.600
THAT THEY COULDN'T
FORESEE THE FUTURE.

00:18:55.600 --> 00:18:58.780
AND THEY EXPLICITLY
PROVIDED FOR THAT REALITY

00:18:58.780 --> 00:19:00.600
IN THE DESIGN OF
THE CONSTITUTION.

00:19:00.600 --> 00:19:01.840
AND HERE'S WHAT THEY DID.

00:19:01.840 --> 00:19:08.120
THEY DID SO BY GIVING CONGRESS
PRIMARY AND BROAD AUTHORITY

00:19:08.120 --> 00:19:12.660
TO ADAPT FEDERAL POWER
TO UNFORESEEABLE CHANGE.

00:19:12.660 --> 00:19:15.620
AS THAT OTHER CHIEF
JUSTICE MARSHALL

00:19:15.620 --> 00:19:20.880
SAID IN A FAMOUS OPINION CALLED
McCULLOCK VS. MARYLAND WHICH

00:19:20.880 --> 00:19:24.220
UPHELD CONGRESS' POWER
TO CREATE A CENTRAL BANK,

00:19:24.220 --> 00:19:26.720
THE FRAMERS KNEW
THEY COULD NOT DEVISE

00:19:26.720 --> 00:19:31.470
A COMPLEX SET OF RULES FOR
A CONSTITUTION INTENDED

00:19:31.470 --> 00:19:34.080
TO ENDURE FOR THE AGES.

00:19:34.080 --> 00:19:35.750
THEY DID SET OUT SOME RULES.

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:37.720
THE PRESIDENT HAS TO BE 35.

00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:39.970
LEGISLATION HAS
TO PASS 2 HOUSES.

00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:43.280
EACH STATE GETS TWO
SENATORS AND SO FORTH.

00:19:43.280 --> 00:19:47.120
AND THOSE RULES CONGRESS CAN'T
MESS WITH NO MATTER HOW THE

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:48.850
WORLD CHANGES.

00:19:48.850 --> 00:19:51.940
BUT FOR MOST ASPECTS
OF OUR GOVERNMENT,

00:19:51.940 --> 00:19:54.340
THE FRAMERS SAID VERY LITTLE.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:56.740
THEY MOSTLY LEFT
THE DETAILS BLANK,

00:19:56.740 --> 00:19:59.590
AND THEY ADOPTED SOMETHING
CALLED THE NECESSARY AND PROPER

00:19:59.590 --> 00:20:03.690
CLAUSE THAT GIVES
CONGRESS PRIMARY AUTHORITY

00:20:03.690 --> 00:20:04.990
TO FILL IN THOSE BLANKS.

00:20:04.990 --> 00:20:08.430
AND CHIEF JUSTICE MARSHALL'S
WORDS, QUOTE TO AVAIL ITSELF

00:20:08.430 --> 00:20:13.050
OF EXPERIENCE, TO EXERCISE
ITS REASON, AND TO ACCOMMODATE

00:20:13.050 --> 00:20:16.820
LEGISLATION TO
NEW CIRCUMSTANCES.

00:20:16.820 --> 00:20:20.880
IT WAS TO BE THE AMERICAN
PEOPLE SPEAKING THROUGH CONGRESS

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:26.500
AND NOT THE JUSTICES WHO WERE TO
FIGURE OUT HOW, WHAT GOVERNMENT

00:20:26.500 --> 00:20:31.370
MEASURES WERE APPROPRIATE AS
AMERICA PASSES INTO NEW AGES

00:20:31.370 --> 00:20:33.990
AND NEW WORLDS.

00:20:33.990 --> 00:20:36.230
SOMETHING LIKE THE INDIVIDUAL
MANDATE OR WHATEVER

00:20:36.230 --> 00:20:39.430
THE NEXT INNOVATION MIGHT
BE OFFENDS SOME PARTICULAR

00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:42.900
CONSTITUTIONAL TEXT OR
LONG STANDING PRACTICE.

00:20:42.900 --> 00:20:45.496
IF CONGRESS WERE TO PASS A
LAW AUTHORIZING MATURE 34 YEAR

00:20:45.496 --> 00:20:51.120
OLDS TO BECOME PRESIDENT, THEN
THE COURT CAN AND MUST SAY NO.

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:56.270
BUT IF THE COURT HAS LITTLE
MORE TO GO ON THAN ITS OWN SENSE

00:20:56.270 --> 00:20:59.950
THAT THIS OR THAT ARRANGEMENT
IS TOO NOVEL, THAT IT GIVES

00:20:59.950 --> 00:21:04.340
CONGRESS TOO MUCH POWER, OR IT
IS SOMETHING THAT THE FRAMERS

00:21:04.340 --> 00:21:08.130
WOULD NOT HAVE COUNTENANCED
IN THE WORLD THAT THEY KNEW,

00:21:08.130 --> 00:21:11.560
THEN THE COURT IS MAKING
A JUDGMENT CALL THAT THE

00:21:11.560 --> 00:21:16.310
CONSTITUTION EXPLICITLY
RESERVES TO CONGRESS.

00:21:16.310 --> 00:21:20.510
IN CASES LIKE SEBELIUS IT
IS PRECISELY THIS ALLOCATION

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:24.120
OF DECISION MAKING POWER
THAT SHOULD BE FOREMOST

00:21:24.120 --> 00:21:25.870
IN THE COURT'S DELIBERATIONS.

00:21:25.870 --> 00:21:27.862
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

00:21:38.200 --> 00:21:38.700
[APPLAUSE]

00:21:38.700 --> 00:21:40.780
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL:
THANK YOU JOHN.

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:44.047
AND I DO HAVE TO SAY I DID SEE
YOU REACHING FOR THE SPINACH

00:21:44.047 --> 00:21:44.880
QUICHE THIS MORNING.

00:21:47.800 --> 00:21:50.840
AS YOU KNOW, WHAT WE'RE GOING TO
DO IS GO BACKWARDS AND FORWARDS

00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:53.650
BETWEEN QUESTIONS
FROM AMONG OURSELVES,

00:21:53.650 --> 00:21:55.290
AND ALSO QUESTIONS FROM YOU.

00:21:55.290 --> 00:21:58.280
THERE ARE NOTE CARDS IF YOU
HAVE ANY PLEASE PASS THEM

00:21:58.280 --> 00:22:00.080
ALONG AND SOMEBODY WILL
COME AND PICK THEM.

00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:01.260
RAISE YOUR HAND.

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:03.500
AND THE PEOPLE AT THE
BACK, IF YOU CAN'T HEAR,

00:22:03.500 --> 00:22:08.570
PLEASE WAVE LIKE CRAZY
AND WE'LL TRY TO FIX THAT.

00:22:08.570 --> 00:22:11.790
I HAVE ONE QUESTION, AND ANY OF
THE THREE OF YOU CAN ANSWER IT.

00:22:11.790 --> 00:22:16.480
ONE OF THE POINTS THAT JOHN
MADE IS THAT THIS COURT,

00:22:16.480 --> 00:22:20.590
THE ROBERTS COURT HAS BEEN
SECOND GUESSING CONGRESS' POWER

00:22:20.590 --> 00:22:22.610
TO A REMARKABLE EXTENT.

00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:24.720
IS THIS NEW?

00:22:24.720 --> 00:22:27.950
I MEAN FOR THOSE OF US WHO
THINK ABOUT THE PRE NEW DEAL,

00:22:27.950 --> 00:22:30.800
IS THIS A DIFFERENT
WAY THAT THE COURT

00:22:30.800 --> 00:22:35.300
IS VIEWING ITS RELATIONSHIP
WITH ANOTHER BRANCH?

00:22:35.300 --> 00:22:37.730
MICHAEL?

00:22:37.730 --> 00:22:39.750
IF YOU DON'T WANT
TO TALK, LAUREN.

00:22:39.750 --> 00:22:43.820
&gt;&gt; MICHAEL KLARMAN: IT'S
NEW, BUT IT'S NOT BRAND NEW.

00:22:43.820 --> 00:22:45.990
THE SUPREME COURT
RARELY CHALLENGE

00:22:45.990 --> 00:22:48.910
CONGRESSIONAL LEGISLATION
IN THE 19TH CENTURY.

00:22:48.910 --> 00:22:51.330
THEY STRUCK DOWN A STATUTE
IN MARBURY VS. MADISON,

00:22:51.330 --> 00:22:54.030
THE FIRST CASE TO DECLARE
THE POWER OF JUDICIAL REVIEW.

00:22:54.030 --> 00:22:56.450
THEY DIDN'T STRIKE DOWN ANOTHER
FEDERAL STATUTE UNTIL DRED

00:22:56.450 --> 00:22:56.950
SCOTT.

00:22:56.950 --> 00:22:59.450
THE INFAMOUS CASE OF
CONGRESS TRYING TO

00:22:59.450 --> 00:23:02.200
KEEP SLAVERY OUT OF THE
MISSOURI COMPROMISE TERRITORY.

00:23:02.200 --> 00:23:05.480
THE TERRITORY ACQUIRED IN
THE LOUISIANA PURCHASE.

00:23:05.480 --> 00:23:08.150
BUT CONGRESS, THE COURT RARELY
STRUCK DOWN CONGRESSIONAL

00:23:08.150 --> 00:23:10.334
LEGISLATION UNTIL
THE 20TH CENTURY.

00:23:10.334 --> 00:23:13.000
IT'S SOMETHING THAT HAS HAPPENED
FAIRLY REGULARLY IN THE LAST 40

00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:13.560
YEARS.

00:23:13.560 --> 00:23:15.726
I DON'T THINK IT'S DISTINCTIVE
TO THE ROBERTS COURT.

00:23:15.726 --> 00:23:17.510
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL:
OTHER COMMENTS?

00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:24.500
&gt;&gt; WHAT'S ALWAYS INTRIGUED ME
ABOUT THE CHIEF JUSTICE'S ROLE

00:23:24.500 --> 00:23:31.350
IN SEBELIUS IN WHAT MOTIVATED
HIM TO BOTH GRATUITOUSLY

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:33.080
EXPRESS HIS VIEWS ON
THE COMMERCE CLAUSE,

00:23:33.080 --> 00:23:36.030
AND JUSTICE GINSBURG WROTE A
FABULOUS DISSENTING OPINION ON

00:23:36.030 --> 00:23:36.530
THAT CASE.

00:23:36.530 --> 00:23:42.810
POINTING OUT THAT ENITRE
COMMERCE CLAUSE DISPOSITION

00:23:42.810 --> 00:23:44.470
WAS GRATUITOUS.

00:23:44.470 --> 00:23:50.030
WHAT MOTIVATED HIM TO DO THAT
AND THEN TO PULL BACK AND FIND

00:23:50.030 --> 00:23:54.090
A DEUS EX MACHINA IN THE
FORM OF THE TAX POWER

00:23:54.090 --> 00:23:56.067
TO SAVE THE STATUTE AND
MAYBE SAVE THE COURT.

00:23:56.067 --> 00:23:57.400
I DON'T KNOW, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

00:23:57.400 --> 00:24:00.670
&gt;&gt; I FIND IT A PUZZLE.

00:24:00.670 --> 00:24:01.170
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:01.170 --> 00:24:06.660
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: ALSO KNOWN
AS TAKING THE 5TH AMENDMENT.

00:24:06.660 --> 00:24:07.260
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:12.300
&gt;&gt; THERE'S ONE PERSON IN THIS
TENT WHO KNOWS THE ANSWER AND

00:24:12.300 --> 00:24:13.210
SHE'S NOT TELLING US.

00:24:13.210 --> 00:24:13.709
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:13.709 --> 00:24:20.540
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: ON
THAT NOTE, MS. GREENHOUSE,

00:24:20.540 --> 00:24:23.820
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
PROCEED WITH YOUR CASE?

00:24:23.820 --> 00:24:25.010
PARENTS INVOLVED.

00:24:25.010 --> 00:24:31.020
&gt;&gt; OKAY, I HAVE LESS OF A FORMAL
ACADEMIC PRESENTATION THAN JOHN

00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:32.790
DID.

00:24:32.790 --> 00:24:36.870
BUT WHAT I'M GOING TO SAY
IS NOT DISCONNECTED FROM HIS

00:24:36.870 --> 00:24:39.084
PRESENTATION.

00:24:39.084 --> 00:24:41.250
I'M NOT GOING TO GO THROUGH
THE DETAILS OF THE CASE.

00:24:41.250 --> 00:24:44.400
I URGE YOU TO READ MY
CAREFULLY WRITTEN LITTLE

00:24:44.400 --> 00:24:47.250
SUMMARY IN THIS BLUE BOOKLET.

00:24:47.250 --> 00:24:51.920
EXAMPLE OF JUDICIAL
ACTIVISM IN ANOTHER FRAME.

00:24:51.920 --> 00:24:54.170
THIS WASN'T THE COURT
AGAINST CONGRESS.

00:24:54.170 --> 00:24:58.080
THIS WAS THE COURT AGAINST LOCAL
CONTROL OF THE PUBLIC SCHOOLS.

00:24:58.080 --> 00:25:02.660
THE ROBERTS COURT HAS
HAD MAYBE 700 DECISIONS

00:25:02.660 --> 00:25:04.710
ON THE MERITS IN THE 10 YEARS.

00:25:04.710 --> 00:25:06.380
ADN THE WAY THIS
PANEL WAS ORGANIZED

00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:08.640
WAS THAT CHIEF JUSTICE
MARSHALL INVITED EACH OF US

00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:11.180
TO SELECT ONE CASE
TO TALK ABOUT.

00:25:11.180 --> 00:25:13.400
SO WHY DID I CHOOSE
PARENTS INVOLVED?

00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:19.040
I CHOSE IT BECAUSE I THINK IT'S
VERY EMBLEMATIC OF A DISTURBING

00:25:19.040 --> 00:25:22.370
ASPECT OF THE ROBERTS COURT.

00:25:22.370 --> 00:25:25.760
I HATE TO USE THE
CLICHED WORD ACTIVISM.

00:25:25.760 --> 00:25:34.230
IT WAS ASSERTION OF JURISDICTION
BY THE COURT TO EVEN DECIDE

00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:34.820
THIS CASE.

00:25:34.820 --> 00:25:41.150
SO YOU KNOW THE BASIC METRIC
THAT THE COURT APPLIES IN

00:25:41.150 --> 00:25:45.550
DECIDING WHETHER IT SHOULD
EXERCISE ITS ALMOST COMPLETE

00:25:45.550 --> 00:25:49.480
DISCRETION ON WHAT TO DECIDE
IS WHETHER THERE'S A CASE THAT

00:25:49.480 --> 00:25:51.330
PRESENTS A CONFLICT
AMONG THE LOWER

00:25:51.330 --> 00:25:54.290
COURTS ON AN IMPORTANT
MATTER OF FEDERAL LAW.

00:25:54.290 --> 00:25:58.640
THERE ACTUALLY WAS NO CONFLICT
ON THE QUESTION OF WHETHER A

00:25:58.640 --> 00:26:03.230
SCHOOL BOARD SEEKING TO PRESERVE
INTEGRATION, NOT TO PRESERVE

00:26:03.230 --> 00:26:07.300
SEGREGATION, TO PRESERVE THE
HARD WON GAINS OF INTEGRATION

00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:13.360
ACHIEVED THROUGH STRUGGLE
AND FEDERAL COURT SUPERVISION

00:26:13.360 --> 00:26:15.440
AND IN THESE CASES
BUSING ORDERS AND SO ON.

00:26:15.440 --> 00:26:18.840
THEY FINALLY GET A MEASURE
OF INTEGRATION AND THEY

00:26:18.840 --> 00:26:19.930
WANT TO KEEP IT.

00:26:19.930 --> 00:26:23.680
AND THERE ARE RESIDENTIAL
HOUSING PATTERNS THAT MAKE IT

00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:25.012
VERY DIFFICULT TO KEEP IT.

00:26:25.012 --> 00:26:26.720
THERE ARE SOCIAL TRENDS
THAT MAKE IT VERY

00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:28.020
DIFFICULT TO KEEP IT.

00:26:28.020 --> 00:26:31.620
SO IN THIS CASE, BOTH THE
CITY, AND THE SCHOOL BOARD

00:26:31.620 --> 00:26:32.750
OF LOUISVILLE, KENTUCKY.

00:26:32.750 --> 00:26:37.190
OF COURSE ONCE A
SEGREGATED CITY.

00:26:37.190 --> 00:26:39.620
AND THE SCHOOL BOARD
OF SEATTLE, WASHINGTON.

00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:41.100
NEVER SEGREGATED.

00:26:41.100 --> 00:26:45.380
BUT HIGHLY RACIALLY
ISOLATED SCHOOLS BECAUSE

00:26:45.380 --> 00:26:47.630
OF HOUSING PATTERNS HAD
BEEN UNDER COURT ORDERS

00:26:47.630 --> 00:26:49.080
FOR MANY YEARS.

00:26:49.080 --> 00:26:54.590
DECIDED THAT IN MODEST WAYS IN
TERMS OF STUDENTS DECIDING THAT

00:26:54.590 --> 00:26:58.160
THEY WANTED TO TRANSFER FROM ONE
SCHOOL TO ANOTHER, OR CHOOSING

00:26:58.160 --> 00:27:02.450
ONE HIGH SCHOOL OR ANOTHER
HIGH SCHOOL, THE SCHOOL BOARD

00:27:02.450 --> 00:27:06.860
WAS ENTITLED TO TAKE RACE
INTO ACCOUNT TO PRESERVE,

00:27:06.860 --> 00:27:10.660
TO PREVENT A RETURN TO
RACIALLY ISOLATED SCHOOLS

00:27:10.660 --> 00:27:12.220
AND CLASSROOMS.

00:27:12.220 --> 00:27:14.240
THIS ISSUE HAS COME
UP AROUND THE COUNTRY,

00:27:14.240 --> 00:27:19.950
AND THE LOWER COURTS ALL
AGREED THIS WAS SOMETHING

00:27:19.950 --> 00:27:27.060
THAT SCHOOL BOARDS COULD CHOOSE
TO DO FOR THIS BENIGN PURPOSE.

00:27:27.060 --> 00:27:31.000
BEFORE JUSTICE O'CONNOR
LEFT THE COURT IN LATE 2005,

00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:34.080
SUCH A CASE CAME UP TO
THE COURT FROM THIS REGION

00:27:34.080 --> 00:27:37.860
TO THE FIRST CIRCUIT, AND THE
COURT DECIDED NOT TO HEAR IT.

00:27:37.860 --> 00:27:40.440
BECAUSE IT DIDN'T MEET THE
USUAL TESTS OF CONFLICT IN THE

00:27:40.440 --> 00:27:40.940
CIRCUIT.

00:27:40.940 --> 00:27:46.220
AS SOON AS O'CONNOR LEFT
THE COURT, IN EARLY 2006,

00:27:46.220 --> 00:27:53.190
THESE TWO CASES MADE THEIR
WAY ONTO THE COURT'S DOCKET.

00:27:53.190 --> 00:27:56.340
AND THE COURT DECIDED EVEN
THOUGH IT DIDN'T MEET THE USUAL

00:27:56.340 --> 00:27:59.990
CHARACTERISTICS
FOR A WORTHY CASE,

00:27:59.990 --> 00:28:02.670
THE COURT DECIDED TO TAKE IT.

00:28:02.670 --> 00:28:04.900
WHAT DID THEY DECIDE?

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:08.030
IN AN OPINION FOR FOUR JUSTICES
BY CHIEF JUSTICE ROBERTS

00:28:08.030 --> 00:28:10.916
THE COURT SAID THIS IS
BASICALLY JUST BROWN VS.

00:28:10.916 --> 00:28:12.540
BOARD OF EDUCATION
FROM THE OTHER SIDE.

00:28:12.540 --> 00:28:16.240
THIS IS GOVERNMENT
COUNTING BY RACE.

00:28:16.240 --> 00:28:18.390
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

00:28:18.390 --> 00:28:21.050
THE CITIES OF
LOUISVILLE AND SEATTLE

00:28:21.050 --> 00:28:22.560
HAD NO COMPELLING INTEREST.

00:28:22.560 --> 00:28:25.070
AND COMPELLING
INTEREST IS THE TEST

00:28:25.070 --> 00:28:29.270
FOR UNDER THE 14TH AMENDMENT'S
EQUAL PROTECTION GUARANTEE

00:28:29.270 --> 00:28:33.200
WHERE THE GOVERNMENT CAN JUSTIFY
CLASSIFYING PEOPLE BY RACE.

00:28:33.200 --> 00:28:36.720
THERE'S NO COMPELLING INTEREST
IN PRESERVING INTEGRATION.

00:28:36.720 --> 00:28:39.510
HE WROTE FOR ONLY 4
BECAUSE JUSTICE KENNEDY

00:28:39.510 --> 00:28:44.500
WHO AGREED WITH THE OUTCOME,
AND IN FACT HAS NEVER VOTED TO

00:28:44.500 --> 00:28:48.600
UPHOLD ANY RACIAL CATEGORIZATION
ON THE PART OF THE SUPREME

00:28:48.600 --> 00:28:52.020
COURT SAID ACTUALLY IT'S
A LITTLE MORE COMPLICATED

00:28:52.020 --> 00:28:52.910
THAN THAT.

00:28:52.910 --> 00:28:56.470
YOU MAY REMEMBER THE LINE WITH
WHICH CHIEF JUSTICE ROBERTS

00:28:56.470 --> 00:28:57.730
ENDED HIS OPINION.

00:28:57.730 --> 00:29:01.100
HE SAID THE WAY TO GET
BEYOND RACIAL DISCRIMINATING

00:29:01.100 --> 00:29:03.220
ON THE BASIS OF RACE IS
TO STOP DISCRIMINATING ON

00:29:03.220 --> 00:29:04.570
THE BASIS OF RACE.

00:29:04.570 --> 00:29:08.240
THAT'S VERY DEEP AND PROFOUND.

00:29:08.240 --> 00:29:09.490
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:09.490 --> 00:29:12.120
AND JUSTICE KENNEDY SAID IT'S
A LITTLE MORE COMPLICATED

00:29:12.120 --> 00:29:12.900
THAN THAT.

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:16.370
HE SAID OF COURSE THE CITIES OF
LOUISVILLE AND SEATTLE HAVE A

00:29:16.370 --> 00:29:19.440
COMPELLING INTEREST IN
PRESERVING INTEGRATION.

00:29:19.440 --> 00:29:21.660
OBVIOUSLY THEY DO.

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:24.510
THE PROBLEM THAT JUSTICE KENNEDY
FOUND WITH THESE PLANS IS HE

00:29:24.510 --> 00:29:27.240
SAID THEY WEREN'T SUFFICIENTLY
NARROWLY TAILORED.

00:29:27.240 --> 00:29:30.010
NARROW TAILORING IS
THE OTHER MAIN ASPECT

00:29:30.010 --> 00:29:32.080
OF THE 14TH AMENDMENT ANALYSIS.

00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:35.430
THEY WEREN'T SUFFICIENTLY
NARROWLY TAILORED TO MEET THE

00:29:35.430 --> 00:29:37.850
EQUAL PROTECTION DEMANDS
OF THE 14TH AMENDMENT.

00:29:37.850 --> 00:29:40.230
BY THAT HE MEANT THERE
WERE OTHER THINGS

00:29:40.230 --> 00:29:43.260
THAT THE SCHOOL DISTRICTS
MIGHT HAVE DONE OTHER

00:29:43.260 --> 00:29:47.720
THAN CATEGORIZING STUDENTS
ON THE BASIS OF RACE.

00:29:47.720 --> 00:29:52.120
A QUESTION OF WHERE SCHOOL
DISTRICT LINES WERE DRAWN OR

00:29:52.120 --> 00:29:54.890
SCHOOLS WITH SPECIAL PROGRAMS
THAT COULD ATTRACT PEOPLE

00:29:54.890 --> 00:29:55.880
AND SO ON AND SO ON.

00:29:55.880 --> 00:30:00.550
WHETHER THAT'S AT ALL REALISTIC
ON THE GROUND I'M NOT IN A

00:30:00.550 --> 00:30:01.280
POSITION TO SAY.

00:30:01.280 --> 00:30:05.120
BUT IT WAS VERY INTERESTING.

00:30:05.120 --> 00:30:06.620
SO THE OTHER THING
THAT INTERESTS ME

00:30:06.620 --> 00:30:09.600
ABOUT THE CASE OTHER
THAN THE SHEER ACTIVISM

00:30:09.600 --> 00:30:16.380
OF TAKING IT IS THAT THE CHIEF
JUSTICE WAS SO DETERMINED TO

00:30:16.380 --> 00:30:18.100
SAY WHAT HE WANTED TO SAY.

00:30:18.100 --> 00:30:20.410
TO USE THE CASE FOR
THE PURPOSE FOR WHICH

00:30:20.410 --> 00:30:23.720
HE WANTED TO USE IT AND
SAY NO COMPELLING INTEREST.

00:30:23.720 --> 00:30:28.300
AND THIS IS JUST BACKWARD
BROWN VS. BOARD OF EDUCATION,

00:30:28.300 --> 00:30:31.560
HE WASN'T WILLING TO MEET
JUSTICE KENNEDY WHERE JUSTICE

00:30:31.560 --> 00:30:32.680
KENNEDY WAS.

00:30:32.680 --> 00:30:38.211
ALL HE WOULD HAVE HAD TO SAY WAS
WE DON'T HAVE TO DECIDE IF THIS

00:30:38.211 --> 00:30:40.710
IS WHAT HE WANTED TO SAY IS WE
DON'T HAVE TO DECIDE IF THERE

00:30:40.710 --> 00:30:41.950
IS A COMPELLING INTEREST.

00:30:41.950 --> 00:30:44.210
ALL WE HAVE TO FIND
IS THAT THIS REMEDY

00:30:44.210 --> 00:30:47.090
IS NOT NARROWLY TAILORED
TO SERVE THAT INTEREST.

00:30:47.090 --> 00:30:50.560
THAT WOULD HAVE LET HIM
SPEAK FOR A MAJORITY.

00:30:50.560 --> 00:30:55.300
IT WOULD HAVE NOT DECIDED
THE MOST PROFOUND ISSUE

00:30:55.300 --> 00:30:56.110
IN THE CASE.

00:30:56.110 --> 00:30:58.360
AND SO THIS WAS EARLY
IN THE ROBERTS COURT.

00:30:58.360 --> 00:31:01.480
IT WAS A 2007 DECISION.

00:31:01.480 --> 00:31:06.740
AND I THINK IT WAS A
RATHER DISTURBING EARLY

00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:11.330
INDICATION OF HOW HE SAW HIS
ROLE IN BOTH CARRYING OUT

00:31:11.330 --> 00:31:16.320
WHAT I CALL A ROBERTS PROJECT ON
RACE, ON GETTING THE GOVERNMENT

00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:18.780
OUT OF THE BUSINESS OF COUNTING
BY RACE FOR ANY REASON.

00:31:18.780 --> 00:31:22.440
AND SHELBY COUNTY, THE
VOTING RIGHTS ACT CASE

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:24.460
IS NOT ONE OF OUR CASES.

00:31:24.460 --> 00:31:25.930
BUT THAT WAS A MAJOR ONE.

00:31:25.930 --> 00:31:29.460
IT DISABLED APPLICATION OF THE
HEART OF THE VOTING RIGHTS ACT.

00:31:31.590 --> 00:31:34.970
BUT ALSO HIS
UNWILLINGNESS TO BEND

00:31:34.970 --> 00:31:37.950
A LITTLE BIT TO MEET JUSTICE
KENNEDY WHERE JUSTICE

00:31:37.950 --> 00:31:38.790
KENNEDY WAS.

00:31:38.790 --> 00:31:44.040
I'LL CONCLUDE BY SAYING THAT IN
THE INTERVENING YEARS, IN 2015,

00:31:44.040 --> 00:31:46.100
BECAUSE THIS WAS ALL
THE WAY BACK IN 2007,

00:31:46.100 --> 00:31:50.060
I'M NOT SURE WE WOULD SEE THE
SAME BEHAVIOR FROM JOHN ROBERTS

00:31:50.060 --> 00:31:51.680
TODAY.

00:31:51.680 --> 00:31:55.720
THIS SOUNDS CONDESCENDING, AND
I DON'T MEAN FOR IT TO SOUND

00:31:55.720 --> 00:31:57.500
CONDESCENDING, I
RESPECT THE MAN.

00:31:57.500 --> 00:32:02.410
HE HAS MATURED IN HIS ROLE
AS CHIEF JUSTICE AND I THINK

00:32:02.410 --> 00:32:08.800
SEES THE VIRTUE OF NOT HAVING TO
WIN EVERY CASE THAT HE CAN WIN.

00:32:08.800 --> 00:32:12.410
OR IN THIS CASE HE DIDN'T WIN ON
THE COMPELLING INTEREST POINT.

00:32:12.410 --> 00:32:15.680
BUT RATHER TRY TO WORK
A BIT OF A COMPROMISE.

00:32:15.680 --> 00:32:17.950
I THINK WE HAVE SEEN
THAT IN RECENT YEARS

00:32:17.950 --> 00:32:19.280
IN VERY FASCINATING WAYS.

00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:22.140
INCLUDING JUST LAST
TERM, THE CASE THAT

00:32:22.140 --> 00:32:25.980
STRUCK DOWN THE BUBBLE
ZONE AROUND THE ABORTION

00:32:25.980 --> 00:32:28.260
CLINICS IN MASSACHUSETTS LAW.

00:32:28.260 --> 00:32:32.340
HE WROTE A QUITE TEMPERED
OPINION THAT ALLOWED JUSTICE

00:32:32.340 --> 00:32:35.190
GINSBURG AND OTHERS
TO JOIN HIS OPINION.

00:32:35.190 --> 00:32:38.530
I DON'T THINK WE WOULD HAVE
SEEN THAT FROM THE EARLIER CHIEF

00:32:38.530 --> 00:32:41.360
JUSTICE ROBERTS.

00:32:41.360 --> 00:32:42.860
THAT'S WHY I CHOSE
PARENTS INVOLVED.

00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:45.750
THAT'S WHY IT'S A CASE
WORTH THINKING ABOUT

00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:50.450
AND KEEPING IN MIND AS THE
ROBERTS COURT GOES FORWARD.

00:32:50.450 --> 00:32:51.710
&gt;&gt; THANK YOU LINDA.

00:32:51.710 --> 00:33:00.720
[APPLAUSE]

00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:03.150
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: SO
LINDA, JUST TO REASSURE YOU,

00:33:03.150 --> 00:33:06.650
I HOPE THAT ALL CHIEF JUSTICES
MATURE AS THEY GO ALONG.

00:33:06.650 --> 00:33:08.310
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:08.310 --> 00:33:11.370
I WANT TO TELL YOU SOME
OF MY EARLY OPINIONS,

00:33:11.370 --> 00:33:14.740
BUT I'M NOT GOING TO
TELL YOU WHICH ONES.

00:33:14.740 --> 00:33:15.720
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:15.720 --> 00:33:18.150
ONE OF THE THINGS THE UNITED
STATES SUPREME COURT DOES

00:33:18.150 --> 00:33:20.810
IS IT TELLS OTHER
FEDERAL COURTS.

00:33:20.810 --> 00:33:23.840
I HATE TO USE THE TERM LOWER
FEDERAL COURTS, BUT WE OFTEN

00:33:23.840 --> 00:33:28.670
CALL THEM LOWER FEDERAL
COURTS, WHAT TO DO.

00:33:28.670 --> 00:33:30.800
HAVE THERE BEEN
CASES WHERE YOU CAN

00:33:30.800 --> 00:33:33.830
SEE THE FEDERAL COURTS
BECOMING MORE ACTIVE

00:33:33.830 --> 00:33:36.880
BASED ON PARENTS INVOLVED?

00:33:36.880 --> 00:33:40.780
&gt;&gt; LINDA GREENHOUSE:
NO, I WONDERED.

00:33:40.780 --> 00:33:44.490
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: YOU
MENTIONED THE VOTING CASE.

00:33:44.490 --> 00:33:47.130
BUT JUST WHAT'S HAPPENING
IN EDUCATIONAL SYSTEMS?

00:33:47.130 --> 00:33:49.290
&gt;&gt; LINDA GREENHOUSE: YEAH.

00:33:49.290 --> 00:33:51.780
NO, I DON'T HAVE A
GOOD ANSWER FOR THAT.

00:33:51.780 --> 00:33:56.400
I HAVEN'T SEEN OTHER PARENTS
INVOLVED TYPE CASES MAKING

00:33:56.400 --> 00:33:58.270
THERE WAY THROUGH THE SYSTEM.

00:33:58.270 --> 00:34:01.370
MY IMPRESSION IS THAT THINGS ARE
GETTING WORKED OUT AT THE LOCAL

00:34:01.370 --> 00:34:04.180
LEVEL WITHOUT NECCESARILY
GOING TO COURT.

00:34:04.180 --> 00:34:09.610
BUT WE HAVEN'T SEEN THE FINAL
WORD ON AT ALL IS THE GENERAL

00:34:09.610 --> 00:34:11.110
QUESTION OF AFFIRMATIVE ACTION.

00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:15.170
IN HIGHER EDUCATION THERE'S
A CASE PENDING ON THE

00:34:15.170 --> 00:34:18.239
COURT'S DOCKET THAT
WE'LL HEAR ABOUT ANY DAY.

00:34:18.239 --> 00:34:21.330
WHETHER THE COURT IS GOING
TO GET INTO FISHER VS.

00:34:21.330 --> 00:34:22.400
UNIVERSITY OF TEXAS.

00:34:22.400 --> 00:34:24.949
THE UNIVERSITY OF TEXAS
AFFIRMATIVE ACTION CASE,

00:34:24.949 --> 00:34:28.139
WHICH THEY COULDN'T QUITE
DECIDE TWO YEARS AGO,

00:34:28.139 --> 00:34:29.480
SENT BACK TO THE LOWER COURT.

00:34:29.480 --> 00:34:33.469
THE LOWER COURT SAID YEAH WE
KIND OF STANDBY WHAT WE SAID

00:34:33.469 --> 00:34:34.280
BEFORE.

00:34:34.280 --> 00:34:37.362
SO THAT'S A BIG OPEN
QUESTION WHETHER

00:34:37.362 --> 00:34:39.070
THE COURT IS GOING TO
GET BACK INTO THAT.

00:34:39.070 --> 00:34:40.489
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: SURE.

00:34:40.489 --> 00:34:43.960
YOU TALKED, YOU SELECTED THIS
COURT AS A WAY OF INDICATING

00:34:43.960 --> 00:34:47.630
THAT AT LEAST THE CHIEF
JUSTICE, IF NOT THE COURT,

00:34:47.630 --> 00:34:50.510
WILL SORT OF REACH OUT AND
BEND SOME OF THE JURISDICTIONAL

00:34:50.510 --> 00:34:54.159
RULES PERHAPS OR NOT LOOK AT
THE WAY THEY USUALLY TAKE CASES

00:34:54.159 --> 00:34:55.949
AS AN EXAMPLE OF
AN ACTIVIST CASE.

00:34:55.949 --> 00:35:00.140
AND YOU MENTIONED THE CHIEF
JUSTICE'S PROJECT ON RACE.

00:35:00.140 --> 00:35:04.320
ARE THERE OTHER CASES LAUREN OR
MIKE WHERE YOU THINK SHOW ONE

00:35:04.320 --> 00:35:07.150
WAY OR THE OTHER WHAT
HIS VIEW ON RACE IS?

00:35:07.150 --> 00:35:12.420
&gt;&gt; LAUREN SUDEALL LUCAS:
NOT TO HIJACK YOUR QUESTION,

00:35:12.420 --> 00:35:15.369
BUT TO RESPOND TO THAT
QUESTION ALSO ABOUT THE IMPACT,

00:35:15.369 --> 00:35:17.910
THERE'S THE PRESIDENTIAL IMPACT,
BUT I THINK THERE'S ALSO THE

00:35:17.910 --> 00:35:19.501
QUESTION OF SYMBOLIC IMPACT.

00:35:19.501 --> 00:35:21.500
BROWN VS. THE BOARD OF
EDUCATION IS ARGUABLY ONE

00:35:21.500 --> 00:35:25.680
OF THE MOST IMPORTANT CASE THAT
THE SPREME COURT HAS DECIDED

00:35:25.680 --> 00:35:26.960
FROM A SYMBOLIC PERSPECTIVE.

00:35:26.960 --> 00:35:31.650
IN PARENTS INVOLVED, TO TAKE
A CASE THAT IMPORTANT AND SORT

00:35:31.650 --> 00:35:34.350
OF REDEPLOY IT IN A WAY THAT'S
VERY DIFFERENT FROM I THINK

00:35:34.350 --> 00:35:38.321
MANY WILL SEE THE INTENTION
OF BROWN IS REALLY QUITE

00:35:38.321 --> 00:35:38.820
SOMETHING.

00:35:38.820 --> 00:35:41.380
AND THE INTERPLAY BETWEEN THE
OTHER OPINIONS IN THAT CASE

00:35:41.380 --> 00:35:42.620
IS REALLY STARTLING, AS WELL.

00:35:42.620 --> 00:35:44.030
YOU HAVE JUSTICE
THOMAS COMPARING

00:35:44.030 --> 00:35:46.154
WHAT THE SCHOOL DISTRICTS
IN LOUISVILLE AND SEATTLE

00:35:46.154 --> 00:35:49.450
ARE DOING TO WHAT THE
SEGREGATIONISTS DID IN 1954.

00:35:49.450 --> 00:35:52.890
TO MAKE THOSE COMPARISONS, ITS
SORT OF DIVORCED FROM INTENTION

00:35:52.890 --> 00:35:55.040
AND HISTORICAL CONTEXT,
IT'S REALLY HARD

00:35:55.040 --> 00:35:57.790
TO GET ONE'S MIND AROUND.

00:35:57.790 --> 00:35:59.555
AND THE LINE THAT
LINDA MENTIONED,

00:35:59.555 --> 00:36:01.680
THE WAY TO STOP DISCRIMINATION
ON THE BASIS OF RACE

00:36:01.680 --> 00:36:03.638
IS TO STOP DISCRIMINATING
ON THE BASIS OF RACE.

00:36:03.638 --> 00:36:06.730
I THOUGHT JUSTICE SOTOMAYOR
HAS SUCH AN ELOQUENT RESPONSE 7

00:36:06.730 --> 00:36:12.702
YEARS LATER WHEN SHE
SAID THE WAY TO STOP

00:36:12.702 --> 00:36:14.160
DISCRIMINATING ON
THE BASIS OF RACE

00:36:14.160 --> 00:36:16.760
IS TO SPEAK OPENLY AND CANDIDLY
ABOUT RACE AND TO APPLY

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:19.020
THE CONSTITUTION WITH EYES
OPEN TO THE UNFORTUNATE

00:36:19.020 --> 00:36:23.000
EFFECTS OF CENTURIES OF
RACIAL DISCRIMINATION.

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:29.710
[APPLAUSE]

00:36:29.710 --> 00:36:32.160
SO I THINK PARENTS INVOLVED
HAD A VERY IMPORTANT SYMBOLIC

00:36:32.160 --> 00:36:32.660
IMPORTANCE.

00:36:32.660 --> 00:36:37.570
IT HASN'T BEEN CITED, IT STILL
HAD AN INDIRECT INFLUENCE BOTH

00:36:37.570 --> 00:36:39.850
ON THE COURTS AND ALSO THE
PUBLIC AND THE WAY WE THINK

00:36:39.850 --> 00:36:41.170
ABOUT RACE MORE BROADLY.

00:36:41.170 --> 00:36:44.420
&gt;&gt; MICHAEL KLARMAN:
I AGREE WITH THAT.

00:36:44.420 --> 00:36:45.540
I WANT TO ADD SOMETHING.

00:36:45.540 --> 00:36:48.040
LINDA'S POINT IS IT
PROCEDURALLY ACTIVIST

00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:49.910
FOR THE COURT TO RESOLVE
THIS QUESTION WHEN

00:36:49.910 --> 00:36:51.500
THERE WAS NO PRESSING NEED.

00:36:51.500 --> 00:36:53.890
IT'S ALSO IMPORTANT TO
UNDERSTAND ITS SUBSTANTIVELY

00:36:53.890 --> 00:36:55.560
ACTIVIST.

00:36:55.560 --> 00:36:57.336
THE CONSERVATIVE
JUSTICES WHO ARE

00:36:57.336 --> 00:36:59.710
THE ONES WHO WOULD INSIST THAT
THE CONSTITUTION SHOULD BE

00:36:59.710 --> 00:37:05.960
COLOR BLIND ARE THE ONES WHO
WOULD CRITICIZE THE COURT IF IT

00:37:05.960 --> 00:37:12.330
STRUCK DOWN AN ABORTION
RESTRICTION OR PERHAPS

00:37:12.330 --> 00:37:14.520
IF THE COURT RULES IN
FAVOR OF GAY MARRIAGE,

00:37:14.520 --> 00:37:17.360
THEY WOULD ACCUSE THE COURT
OF BEING ACTIVISTS FOR READING

00:37:17.360 --> 00:37:20.700
THE CONSTITUTION IN A WAY
THAT INTENDED BY THE PEOPLE

00:37:20.700 --> 00:37:21.760
WHO WROTE IT.

00:37:21.760 --> 00:37:24.230
BUT IT TURNS OUT THAT
THE 14TH AMENDMENT

00:37:24.230 --> 00:37:28.040
WAS NOT CLEARLY INTENDED
TO EMBRACE COLOR BLINDNESS.

00:37:28.040 --> 00:37:31.300
THERE IS NO GOOD HISTORICAL
ARGUMENT THAT THAT'S WHAT THE

00:37:31.300 --> 00:37:33.814
PEOPLE WHO WROTE THE
14TH AMENDMENT INTENDED.

00:37:33.814 --> 00:37:36.230
AND THERE'S NOTHING IN THE
TEXT OF THE 14TH AMENDMENT THAT

00:37:36.230 --> 00:37:39.610
TALKS ABOUT RACE SOME HOW
BEING OFF LIMITS TO GOVERNMENT

00:37:39.610 --> 00:37:41.210
CLASSIFICATION.

00:37:41.210 --> 00:37:43.430
THE PEOPLE WHO WROTE
IT IRONICALLY WERE TOO

00:37:43.430 --> 00:37:48.400
RACIST TO ACTUALLY SUPPORT A
BAN ON RACE CLASSIFICATIONS.

00:37:48.400 --> 00:37:51.060
THEY SAID REPEATEDLY WHEN THEY
WERE ADOPTING THE AMENDMENT

00:37:51.060 --> 00:37:54.200
THAT THIS DOESN'T MANDATE
THAT YOU ENFRANCHISE BLACKS OR

00:37:54.200 --> 00:37:57.900
MANDATE THAT YOU END
SCHOOL SEGREGATION.

00:37:57.900 --> 00:38:00.070
FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF
THE CONSERVATIVE JUSTICES,

00:38:00.070 --> 00:38:03.390
IF THE TEXT OF THE CONSTITUTION
DOESN'T RULE OUT ANY PARTICULAR

00:38:03.390 --> 00:38:06.670
POLICY, AND THE ORIGINAL
UNDERSTANDING OF THAT TEXT

00:38:06.670 --> 00:38:09.620
DOESN'T CLEARLY RULE OUT
A PARTICULAR POLICY THEN

00:38:09.620 --> 00:38:12.680
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO DEFER TO
DEMOCRACY AND DEFER TO LOCAL

00:38:12.680 --> 00:38:13.620
GOVERNMENT.

00:38:13.620 --> 00:38:16.250
AND AS LINDA WAS SAYING,
THIS IS AS LOCAL AS IT GETS.

00:38:16.250 --> 00:38:19.780
THIS IS A LOCAL SCHOOL BOARD
ADOPTING AN INTEGRATIONIST

00:38:19.780 --> 00:38:20.900
POLICY.

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:23.640
THIS IS ACTIVISM NOT
JUST PROCEDURALLY BUT ITS

00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:25.690
SUBSTANTIVE ACTIVISM
FROM THE RIGHT.

00:38:25.690 --> 00:38:28.340
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: GOOD.

00:38:28.340 --> 00:38:29.600
OKAY.

00:38:29.600 --> 00:38:33.740
[APPLAUSE]

00:38:33.740 --> 00:38:36.960
LINDA, LAST WORD, OR
YOU'VE HAD YOUR SAY?

00:38:36.960 --> 00:38:37.460
OKAY.

00:38:37.460 --> 00:38:42.080
LAUREN, SO AGAIN LINDA
SAID WE ASKED EACH OF THEM

00:38:42.080 --> 00:38:48.100
TO SELECT ONE OPINION OF THE TEN
YEARS THAT INDICATED SOMETHING

00:38:48.100 --> 00:38:48.670
IMPORTANT.

00:38:48.670 --> 00:38:49.170
LAUREN?

00:38:49.170 --> 00:38:50.774
&gt;&gt; LAUREN SUDEALL
LUCAS: THANK YOU.

00:38:50.774 --> 00:38:53.190
AND THANK YOU AGAIN DEAN COHEN
AND THE RADCLIFFE INSTITUTE

00:38:53.190 --> 00:38:54.790
FOR HAVING ME HERE TODAY.

00:38:54.790 --> 00:38:56.440
THE CASE THAT I
CHOOSE TO DISCUSS

00:38:56.440 --> 00:38:59.864
FOR MY PORTION OF THE DISCUSSION
IS ASHCROFT VS. IQBAL.

00:38:59.864 --> 00:39:02.280
TO MANY OF YOU THIS CASE MAY
NOT BE AS FAMILIAR BECAUSE IT

00:39:02.280 --> 00:39:04.775
WASN'T ONE THAT RECEIVED A LOT
OF ATTENTION FROM THE MEDIA.

00:39:04.775 --> 00:39:06.900
OR AT LEAST NOT AS MUCH AS
SOME OF THE OTHER CASES.

00:39:06.900 --> 00:39:08.950
BUT IT IS REALY
IMPORTANT IN PART BECAUSE

00:39:08.950 --> 00:39:11.880
IT REPRESENTS AN EMERGING THEME
OF THE ROBERTS COURT WHICH

00:39:11.880 --> 00:39:14.400
IS DEFINING THE ROLE THE COURT
PLAYS IN MUCH NARROWER TERMS

00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:16.040
AND RESTRICTING
PLAINTIFFS ACCESS

00:39:16.040 --> 00:39:17.550
TO THE COURTS AND
ACCESS TO JUSTICE,

00:39:17.550 --> 00:39:20.625
PARTICULARLY FOR INDIVIDUAL
AND PRO SLAVE PLAINTIFFS.

00:39:20.625 --> 00:39:23.000
THE CASES THAT MY CO-PANELISTS
TODAY HAVE DISCUSSED TODAY

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:25.166
HIGHLIGHT FOR GOOD REASONS
SOME OF THE LARGER SOCIAL

00:39:25.166 --> 00:39:28.160
AND POLITICAL ISSUES THAT THE
COURT HAS CONFRONTED OVER THE

00:39:28.160 --> 00:39:29.459
LAST DECADE.

00:39:29.459 --> 00:39:31.750
A LOT OF THE CASES THAT THE
COURT HEARS HOWEVER INVOLVE

00:39:31.750 --> 00:39:33.460
PROCEDURAL AND
JURISDICTIONAL QUESTIONS THAT

00:39:33.460 --> 00:39:35.751
AREN'T PARTICULARLY EXCITING
AND DON'T ATTRACT A LOT OF

00:39:35.751 --> 00:39:37.507
ATTENTION OUTSIDE LEGAL CIRCLES.

00:39:37.507 --> 00:39:39.340
BUT THEY GO TO THE
DEEPER IMPORTANT QUESTION

00:39:39.340 --> 00:39:42.740
OF WHETHER A COURT CAN ENTERTAIN
A CLAIM AND WHO CAN ASSERT SUCH

00:39:42.740 --> 00:39:43.720
A CLAIM.

00:39:43.720 --> 00:39:46.400
THESE QUESTIONS ARE PRECURSORS
THAT WE HAVE TO ANSWER BEFORE

00:39:46.400 --> 00:39:49.130
WE CAN GET TO CASES LIKE
SEBELIUS OR PARENTS INVOLVED.

00:39:49.130 --> 00:39:51.630
IN ADDRESSING THESE QUESTIONS,
ALTHOUGH THERE HAVE BEEN SOME

00:39:51.630 --> 00:39:54.730
ANOMALIES, THE ROBERTS COURT HAS
OFTEN ACTED TO RESTRICT ACCESS

00:39:54.730 --> 00:39:55.930
TO THE COURTS.

00:39:55.930 --> 00:39:58.600
TO PROVIDE A FEW EXAMPLES IN
WHICH THE ROBERTS COURT HAS

00:39:58.600 --> 00:40:00.550
ALREADY HAD AN IMPACT.

00:40:00.550 --> 00:40:03.220
FIRST THE ROBERTS COURT HAS
BROADLY INTERPRETED ARBITRATION

00:40:03.220 --> 00:40:05.860
AGREEMENTS TO PREVENT INJURED
INDIVIDUALS FROM GOING TO

00:40:05.860 --> 00:40:08.330
COURT, INSTEAD CHANNELING
THEM INTO ARBITRATION

00:40:08.330 --> 00:40:10.080
AND RESTRICTING THEIR
ABILITY TO VINDICATE

00:40:10.080 --> 00:40:11.750
THEIR RIGHTS IN THAT CONTEXT.

00:40:11.750 --> 00:40:13.900
AND THE COURT HAS PREVENTED
HABEUS PETITIONERS

00:40:13.900 --> 00:40:16.570
WHO PRESENTING NEW EVIDENCE
IN FEDERAL COURT EVEN EVIDENCE

00:40:16.570 --> 00:40:19.170
REGARDING ACTUAL INNOCENCE
OR PROSECUTORIAL MISCONDUCT

00:40:19.170 --> 00:40:19.720
HAS OCCURED.

00:40:19.720 --> 00:40:22.136
INSTEAD THEY'RE LIMITED TO THE
RECORD AS IT EXISTED IN THE

00:40:22.136 --> 00:40:22.872
STATE COURT.

00:40:22.872 --> 00:40:24.330
THE COURT HAS
LIMITED THE INSTANCES

00:40:24.330 --> 00:40:26.750
IN WHICH INDIVIDUALS CAN
SUE STATES IN FEDERAL COURT

00:40:26.750 --> 00:40:29.360
TO CHALLENGE UNCONSTITUTIONAL
STATE ACTION.

00:40:29.360 --> 00:40:31.900
THERE ARE OTHER EXAMPLES AND
THE LAST THAT I'LL MENTION AND

00:40:31.900 --> 00:40:34.555
WE'RE FOCUSED ON TODAY IS THAT
THE COURT HAS RAISED THE BAR

00:40:34.555 --> 00:40:36.680
FOR WHAT A PLAINTIFF HAS
TO ALLEGE AT THE OUTSET OF

00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:39.380
LITIGATION IN ORDER TO AVOID
BEING THROWN OUT OF COURT

00:40:39.380 --> 00:40:40.970
ALTOGETHER.

00:40:40.970 --> 00:40:43.640
IQBAL AS THE DESCRIPTION
IN YOUR PROGRAM SAYS

00:40:43.640 --> 00:40:47.730
AROSE IN THE WAKE OF 911, IQBAL
WAS CHALLENGING HIS TREATMENT

00:40:47.730 --> 00:40:50.230
BY THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT
WHILE HE WAS BEING DETAINED.

00:40:50.230 --> 00:40:51.730
THE COURT NEVER
REACHED THE QUESTION

00:40:51.730 --> 00:40:54.040
OF WHETHER HIS TREATMENT WAS
ACTUALLY UNCONSTITUTIONAL.

00:40:54.040 --> 00:40:56.930
INSTEAD THE PRECURSOR QUESTION
AND THE ONLY QUESTION THE COURT

00:40:56.930 --> 00:40:59.830
DID ANSWER WAS WHETHER
HE HAD ALLEGED SUFFICIENT

00:40:59.830 --> 00:41:03.190
FACTS IN HIS COMPLAINT TO
SURVIVE A MOTION TO DISMISS.

00:41:03.190 --> 00:41:05.750
FOR THOSE WHO AREN'T LAWYERS,
WHEN A PLAINTIFF WISHES TO

00:41:05.750 --> 00:41:07.360
INITIATE A LAWSUIT
IN FEDERAL COURT,

00:41:07.360 --> 00:41:09.394
INITIALLY SHE FILES A COMPLAINT.

00:41:09.394 --> 00:41:11.060
AND THEN YOU WOULD
PROGRESS TO DISCOVERY

00:41:11.060 --> 00:41:13.018
WHERE THE TWO SIDES WOULD
EXCHANGE INFORMATION,

00:41:13.018 --> 00:41:15.920
AND THEN, AT LEAST IN THEORY,
LEAD POTENTIALLY TO TRIAL.

00:41:15.920 --> 00:41:19.500
THESE CASES ARE ABOUT
THE TRANSITION FROM THAT

00:41:19.500 --> 00:41:20.780
FIRST TO THAT SECOND STEP.

00:41:20.780 --> 00:41:23.010
HAD THE PLAINTIFF DONE
ENOUGH OF PRESENTED ENOUGH

00:41:23.010 --> 00:41:26.740
IN HER COMPLAINT TO JUSTIFY
MOVING ONTO DISCOVERY.

00:41:26.740 --> 00:41:28.740
SO THE FEDERAL RULES OF
OFFICIAL PROCEDURE STATE

00:41:28.740 --> 00:41:30.820
THAT A COMPLAINANT MUST
PROVIDE A SHORT AND PLAIN

00:41:30.820 --> 00:41:31.870
STATEMENT OF THE CLAIM.

00:41:31.870 --> 00:41:34.381
SHOWING THAT THE PLEADER
IS ENTITLED TO RELIEF.

00:41:34.381 --> 00:41:36.630
FOR DECADES THIS WAS UNDERSTOOD
TO BE A FAIRLY LENIENT

00:41:36.630 --> 00:41:39.010
STANDARD, JUST PUTTING THE OTHER
SIDE ON NOTICE OF THE CLAIM,

00:41:39.010 --> 00:41:40.870
WAS OFTEN REFERRED TO
AS NOTICE PLEADING.

00:41:40.870 --> 00:41:42.740
JUST GIVING THEM A
HEADS UP OF WHAT WOULD

00:41:42.740 --> 00:41:44.970
BE INVOLVED IN THE LITIGATION.

00:41:44.970 --> 00:41:48.090
TWO YEARS BEFORE IQBAL IN A
CASE OF BELL ATLANTIC CORP. VS.

00:41:48.090 --> 00:41:49.820
TWOMBLY, THE COURT
RAISED THAT STANDARD

00:41:49.820 --> 00:41:52.350
IN AN ANTITRUST CONTEXT
BUT IT WASNT CLEAR

00:41:52.350 --> 00:41:54.325
IF IT WOULD BE APPLIED
BEYOND THAT CONTEXT.

00:41:54.325 --> 00:41:56.950
IN TWOMBLY, THE COURT SAID THAT
HAD THE JUDGE DETERMINED AT THE

00:41:56.950 --> 00:41:58.408
OUTSET OF THE CASE,
WHETHER THERE'S

00:41:58.408 --> 00:42:00.106
A PLAUSIBLE CLAIM FOR RELEIF.

00:42:00.106 --> 00:42:02.480
SO INTERJECTING SOME JUDGMENT
THERE, NOT JUST PUTTIN GHTE

00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:04.510
OTHER SIDE ON NOTICE,
BUT ALLOWING THE JUDGE

00:42:04.510 --> 00:42:08.070
TO EXERCISE DISCRETION AS TO
WHY THIS IS REALLY PLAUSIBLE.

00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:10.700
IQBAL TOOK A FURTHER STEP
MAKING SURE THAT STANDARD WOULD

00:42:10.700 --> 00:42:13.820
APPLY TO ALL CIVIL
CASES IN FEDERAL COURT.

00:42:13.820 --> 00:42:16.440
WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE, BEFORE
A PLAINTIFF'S ALLEGATIONS WERE

00:42:16.440 --> 00:42:18.510
PRESUMED TO BE TRUE AND A
COMPLAINT WOULD BE DISMISSED

00:42:18.510 --> 00:42:20.385
ONLY IF THERE WERE NO
SET OF FACTS THAT WOULD

00:42:20.385 --> 00:42:22.180
ENTITLE THE PLAINTIFF TO RELIEF.

00:42:22.180 --> 00:42:24.230
BUT IN IQBAL, THE STANDARD
PROVIDES LOWER COURTS

00:42:24.230 --> 00:42:26.521
WITH MUCH GREATER JUDICIAL
DISCRETION AND IT'S REALLY A

00:42:26.521 --> 00:42:28.230
VERY SUBJECTIVE DETERMINATION.

00:42:28.230 --> 00:42:31.540
THE COURT SUGGESTED THAT A
REVIEWING COURT SHOULD DRAW ON

00:42:31.540 --> 00:42:34.260
THEIR JUDICIAL EXPERIENCE AND
COMMON SENSE WHEN MAKING SUCH A

00:42:34.260 --> 00:42:36.510
DETERMINATION, AND I'LL TOUCH
ON THAT LATER IN THE WAY

00:42:36.510 --> 00:42:40.310
IT'S ALLOWED BIAS TO FILTER
INTO MAKING THE DETERMINATIONS

00:42:40.310 --> 00:42:43.360
WHETHER A COMPLAINT, WHETHER
A CLAIM AND COMPLAINT IS

00:42:43.360 --> 00:42:43.900
PLAUSIBLE.

00:42:43.900 --> 00:42:45.861
THIS ALL MAY SEEM TECHNICAL.

00:42:45.861 --> 00:42:48.110
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT PLEADING
STANDARDS AND COMPLAINTS.

00:42:48.110 --> 00:42:49.910
WHY DOES IT MATTER?

00:42:49.910 --> 00:42:52.730
IQBAL WAS CITED MORE THAN
500 TIMES IN THE 2 MONTHS

00:42:52.730 --> 00:42:53.700
FOLLOWING THE DECISION.

00:42:53.700 --> 00:42:58.384
JUST 8 MONTHS LATER, IN
8,000 LOWER COURT CASES.

00:42:58.384 --> 00:42:59.800
AT ONLY TWO YEARS
OLD, TWOMBLY WAS

00:42:59.800 --> 00:43:03.990
ONE OF THE 5 MOST CITED COURT
CASES IN LOWER FEDERAL COURTS

00:43:03.990 --> 00:43:05.349
IN ALL OF AMERICAN HISTORY.

00:43:05.349 --> 00:43:07.390
THEY REALLY GRASPED ON
THIS AS IMPORTANT AND THEN

00:43:07.390 --> 00:43:09.223
IT'S OBVIOUSLY SOMETHING
THAT THEY SHOULD BE

00:43:09.223 --> 00:43:11.460
FOLLOWING AND ACCESSING
COMPLAINTS BEFORE THEM.

00:43:11.460 --> 00:43:13.250
ONE PROMINENT SUPREME
COURT LITIGATOR

00:43:13.250 --> 00:43:15.410
SAID IQBAL WAS THE MOST
SIGNIFICANT SUPREME COURT

00:43:15.410 --> 00:43:17.410
DECISION IN A DECADE FOR
DAY TO DAY LITIGATION

00:43:17.410 --> 00:43:18.981
IN THE FEDERAL COURTS.

00:43:18.981 --> 00:43:21.480
THERE ARE A NUMBER OF STUDIES
ACCESSING THE IMPACT THAT IT'S

00:43:21.480 --> 00:43:23.170
HAD IN TERMS OF CLAIMS
BEING DISMISSED.

00:43:23.170 --> 00:43:25.040
JUST TO GIVE YOU A FEW NUMBERS.

00:43:25.040 --> 00:43:27.820
THE OVERALL RATE OF
DISMISSAL WENT FROM 61%

00:43:27.820 --> 00:43:30.440
PRE TWOMBLY TO 72% IQBAL.

00:43:30.440 --> 00:43:33.290
AND AN IMPACT HAS BEEN
FELT MORE STRONGLY

00:43:33.290 --> 00:43:36.240
AND DEEPLY IN CASES INVOLVED
CIVIL RIGHTS DISCRIMINATION,

00:43:36.240 --> 00:43:38.230
EMPLOYMENT DISCRIMINATION,
AND IN PRISON,

00:43:38.230 --> 00:43:41.660
AND IN CASES INVOLVING PRO SE
PLAINTIFFS OR PLAINTIFFS THAT

00:43:41.660 --> 00:43:43.880
ARE SERVING AS THEIR OWN LAYWER.

00:43:43.880 --> 00:43:45.930
SO IN CIVIL RIGHTS
CASES THAT ARE PRO SE,

00:43:45.930 --> 00:43:50.180
THE DISMISSAL RATE
WENT FROM 85% TO 92%.

00:43:50.180 --> 00:43:55.756
IN PRISON CASES 67% TO 85% AND
IN EMPLOYMENT DISCRIMINATION

00:43:55.756 --> 00:43:58.130
CASES WHERE THE PLAINTIFF WAS
REPRESENTED BY COUNCIL FROM

00:43:58.130 --> 00:44:00.590
47% TO 65%.

00:44:00.590 --> 00:44:02.780
ONE OF THE REASONS FOR
THIS UP TICK IN DISMISSALS

00:44:02.780 --> 00:44:05.690
IS THAT OFTEN TO PROVE A CLAIM,
THE PLAINTIFF NEEDS INFORMATION

00:44:05.690 --> 00:44:06.524
FROM THE OTHER SIDE.

00:44:06.524 --> 00:44:09.189
SO FOR EXAMPLE IN DISCRIMINATION
CASES WHERE YOU HAVE TO PROVE A

00:44:09.189 --> 00:44:11.380
DISCRIMINATORY INTENT,
IT'S VERY HARD TO DO THAT,

00:44:11.380 --> 00:44:14.280
PARTICULARLY FOR POOR OR PRO SE
LITIGANTS WHO AREN'T RESOURCED

00:44:14.280 --> 00:44:16.700
AND DON'T HAVE ACCESS TO KNOW
WHAT WAS IN THE MIND OF THE

00:44:16.700 --> 00:44:18.430
DISCRIMINATOR.

00:44:18.430 --> 00:44:21.260
SO BY PREVENTING THEM FROM
GETTING TO THAT NEXT LEVEL OF

00:44:21.260 --> 00:44:23.820
DISCOVERY, YOU'RE REALLY
DISABLING THEM FROM MAKING

00:44:23.820 --> 00:44:26.160
THEIR CLAIM AND THE CLAIM
MAY NOT BE PLAUSIBLE BASED ON

00:44:26.160 --> 00:44:28.080
WHAT'S IN THE COMPLAINT.

00:44:28.080 --> 00:44:29.830
UNDER THE IQBAL STANDARDS
INDIVIDUALS HAVE

00:44:29.830 --> 00:44:32.234
FARED WORSE THAN CORPORATIONS
OR THE GOVERNMENT AND THAT

00:44:32.234 --> 00:44:34.150
ARGUABLY IS IN LINE WITH
WHAT OTHERS HAVE SAID

00:44:34.150 --> 00:44:37.040
IS A TREND OF THE ROBERTS COURT
TO BE PRO CORPORATE OR PRO

00:44:37.040 --> 00:44:38.227
BUSINESS.

00:44:38.227 --> 00:44:40.310
AND AS I MENTIONED EARLIER
THIS IDEA OF RELYING ON

00:44:40.310 --> 00:44:43.640
JUDICIAL EXPERIENCE AND
COMMON SENSE, THAT PROVIDES AN

00:44:43.640 --> 00:44:46.290
AVENUE FOR BIAS WHETHER
CONSCIENCE OR SUBCONSCIENCE TO

00:44:46.290 --> 00:44:50.040
COLOR JUDGE'S CLAIMS
OF WHETHER JUDGES

00:44:50.040 --> 00:44:54.090
ANALYSIS OF WHETHER PLAINTIFF'S
CLAIMS ARE PLAUSIBLE.

00:44:54.090 --> 00:44:56.270
FOR BLACK PLAINTIFFS
CLAIMING RACE DISCRIMINATION,

00:44:56.270 --> 00:44:58.280
THE DISMISSAL RATE
INCREASED FROM 20%

00:44:58.280 --> 00:45:02.820
PRE TWOMBLY TO 54.6% AFTER IQBAL
AND WHITE JUDGES WERE TWO TIMES

00:45:02.820 --> 00:45:05.730
AS LIKELY TO DISMISS THESE
CLAIMS AS BLACK JUDGES.

00:45:05.730 --> 00:45:07.870
SO BY HAVING THIS MORE
SUBJECTIVE STANDARD,

00:45:07.870 --> 00:45:10.480
YOU'RE REALLY ALLOWING THE
JUDGES TO HAVE MUCH GREATER

00:45:10.480 --> 00:45:12.680
DISCRETION ABOUT WHETHER
SOMEONE CAN EVEN PROCEED,

00:45:12.680 --> 00:45:15.737
NOT TO WHETHER THEY'LL WIN, BUT
JUST TO PROCEED TO DISCOVERY.

00:45:15.737 --> 00:45:18.070
SOME OF ARGUES THAT THE TWOMBLY
STANDARD WAS NEVER MEANT

00:45:18.070 --> 00:45:19.450
TO BE INTERPRETED IN THIS WAY.

00:45:19.450 --> 00:45:21.320
ONE INTERESTING POINT
IS THAT JUSTICE SOUTER

00:45:21.320 --> 00:45:24.930
WHO WROTE THE OPINION ON TWOMBLY
ACTUALLY DISSENTED IN IQBAL.

00:45:24.930 --> 00:45:27.430
OTHERS LIKE JUSTICE STEVENS AND
JUSTICE GINSBURG HAVE PUSHED

00:45:27.430 --> 00:45:29.763
BACK ON THE IMPOSITION OF A
HEIGHTENED PLEADING STANDARD

00:45:29.763 --> 00:45:32.590
SAYING THAT THE IDEA BEHIND THE
FEDERAL RULES WAS NEVER TO KEEP

00:45:32.590 --> 00:45:35.629
LITIGANTS OUT OF COURT,
BUT RATHER TO KEEP THEM IN.

00:45:35.629 --> 00:45:37.920
I'LL JUST END BY SAYING THAT
ULTIMATELY AND PART OF THE

00:45:37.920 --> 00:45:40.050
REASON WHY I CHOSE TO HIGHLIGHT
THIS CASE EVEN THOUGH IT

00:45:40.050 --> 00:45:42.190
HASN'T RECEIVED AS MUCH
ATTENTION IS THAT DECISIONS

00:45:42.190 --> 00:45:45.480
LIKE IQBAL ARE EXTREMELY
IMPORTANT AND IMPACTFUL BECAUSE

00:45:45.480 --> 00:45:48.100
THE RIGHTS IN THE CONSTITUTION
HAVE LITTLE MEANING IF THE

00:45:48.100 --> 00:45:51.190
LITIGANTS LACK ACCESS IN THE
COURTS TO VINDICATE THEM.

00:45:51.190 --> 00:46:05.750
[APPLAUSE]

00:46:05.750 --> 00:46:07.500
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL:
SO THANK YOU LAUREN.

00:46:07.500 --> 00:46:10.820
I WONDER HOW MANY OF US REMEMBER
THAT ONE OF THE THINGS THAT

00:46:10.820 --> 00:46:13.440
MADE US A DIFFERENT NATION
FROM ENGLAND IS WE HAVE A

00:46:13.440 --> 00:46:16.420
CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHT
TO GO TO COURT.

00:46:16.420 --> 00:46:17.550
NOT SO IN ENGLAND.

00:46:17.550 --> 00:46:20.310
IT'S VERY, VERY DIFFICULT FOR
PEOPLE TO GET ACCESS TO COURT.

00:46:20.310 --> 00:46:22.940
IT'S WRITTEN IN OUR CONSTITUTION
THAT YOU HAVE A CONSTITUTIONAL

00:46:22.940 --> 00:46:24.050
RIGHT TO GO TO COURT.

00:46:24.050 --> 00:46:27.760
WHEN YOU THINK OF THAT IN
THE CONTEXT OF THIS DECISION,

00:46:27.760 --> 00:46:30.390
IT'S PRETTY STUNNING.

00:46:30.390 --> 00:46:33.330
I HAVE TO SAY LAUREN, I
DIDN'T KNOW THOSE STATS.

00:46:33.330 --> 00:46:35.760
IT TELLS YOU WHAT HAPPENS, IF
YOU THINK OF THE QUESTION I

00:46:35.760 --> 00:46:40.930
ASKED TO LINDA, HOW MANY CASES
FOLLOWED PARENTS UNITED AND YOU

00:46:40.930 --> 00:46:43.450
CAN SEE IMMEDIATELY THE
IMPACT THTA IT'S HAD.

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:49.510
IT IS NOT TRUE THAT THE JUDGES
WOULD LIKE TO HAVE FEWER CASES.

00:46:49.510 --> 00:46:51.880
ACTUALLY, WE WOULD LIKE
TO HAVE FEWER CASES.

00:46:51.880 --> 00:46:53.600
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:53.600 --> 00:46:58.290
I CAN'T BUT HELP TO TAKE A
MOMENT NOW TO SAY SOMETHING

00:46:58.290 --> 00:47:01.360
THAT I SAY ALMOST EVERY
GATHERING THAT I HAVE,

00:47:01.360 --> 00:47:05.550
WHICH IS WHY WE FOCUS
APPROPRIATELY ON THE FEDERAL

00:47:05.550 --> 00:47:08.420
COURTS AND OF COURSE ON THE
UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT.

00:47:08.420 --> 00:47:12.220
SO MANY CASES ARE
DECIDED IN OUR STATE

00:47:12.220 --> 00:47:14.020
COURTS, WHICH ARE JUST
OVERWHELMED BY THE

00:47:14.020 --> 00:47:15.080
NUMBER OF CASES.

00:47:15.080 --> 00:47:18.570
AND ALTHOUGH WE DON'T
NECESSARILY HAVE TO FOLLOW THE

00:47:18.570 --> 00:47:21.180
UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT
ON A DECISION LIKE THIS,

00:47:21.180 --> 00:47:24.940
IT HAS ENORMOUS INFLUENCE
ON HOW WE DECIDE OUR CASES,

00:47:24.940 --> 00:47:29.520
WHETHER WE DECIDE TO ADMIT
OR TO DISMISS A CASE.

00:47:29.520 --> 00:47:35.280
AND SO THAT EXTRAORDINARY
ORTHOLOGY RIPPLED VERY QUICKLY

00:47:35.280 --> 00:47:37.650
ACROSS THE COUNTRY.

00:47:37.650 --> 00:47:38.710
MICHAEL OR LINDA?

00:47:38.710 --> 00:47:39.220
COMMENTS?

00:47:39.220 --> 00:47:39.870
YEAH, LINDA.

00:47:39.870 --> 00:47:43.360
&gt;&gt; LINDA GREENHOUSE: JUST
ONE COMMENT, THE IQBAL CASE,

00:47:43.360 --> 00:47:47.410
UNLIKE PARENTS INVOLVED, IT'S
NOT A CONSTITUTIONAL DECISION.

00:47:47.410 --> 00:47:49.420
IT'S AN INTERPRETATION
OF THE FEDERAL RULES,

00:47:49.420 --> 00:47:52.590
AND IT'S WITHIN THE POWER
OF CONGRESS TO CHANGE THAT.

00:47:52.590 --> 00:47:56.700
AND THERE HAVE BEEN EFFORTS
TO PASS LEGISLATION THAT WOULD

00:47:56.700 --> 00:48:03.176
REVERSE IQBAL AND RETURN TO THE
MORE LIBERAL PLEADING STANDARD.

00:48:03.176 --> 00:48:05.550
HOW MANY PEOPLE IN THIS ROOM
HAVE EVER HEARD OF THIS CASE

00:48:05.550 --> 00:48:05.590
BEFORE YOU CAME HERE?

00:48:05.590 --> 00:48:05.690
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: THIS IS
A VERY EDUCATED AUDIENCE LINDA.

00:48:05.690 --> 00:48:07.690
I WOULD HAVE PUT UP MY
HAND WHETHER OR NOT I HAD

00:48:07.690 --> 00:48:11.440
