WITH THE LAST QUESTION
ABOUT ACTIVISM.

00:59:17.600 --> 00:59:20.760
AGAIN, IF YOU TAKE AS AN
EXAMPLE ABORTION REGULATION,

00:59:20.760 --> 00:59:23.300
WHEN THE COURT STRIKES DOWN AN
ABORTION REGULATION, JUSTICE

00:59:23.300 --> 00:59:26.350
SCALIA AND THOMAS WOULD SAY,
THE ORIGINAL UNDERSTANDING

00:59:26.350 --> 00:59:28.710
OF THE 14TH AMENDMENT HAS
NOTHING TO DO WITH ABORTION.

00:59:28.710 --> 00:59:31.600
THIS SHOULD BE LEFT UP TO
LEGISLATIVE REGULATION.

00:59:31.600 --> 00:59:35.140
SO THE QUESTION IS, HOW DID
THE FIVE CONSERVATIVE JUSTICES

00:59:35.140 --> 00:59:38.970
JUSTIFY STRIKING DOWN
A BAN ON CORPORATIONS,

00:59:38.970 --> 00:59:42.980
MAKING INDEPENDENT SPEECH
STATEMENTS IN ELECTIONS?

00:59:42.980 --> 00:59:45.842
AND THIS GETS BACK TO
MARGIE'S LAST QUESTION

00:59:45.842 --> 00:59:48.050
WHICH IS HOW WOULD THEY
DEFEND THEMSELVES AGAINST THE

00:59:48.050 --> 00:59:49.660
CHARGES OF ACTIVISM.

00:59:49.660 --> 00:59:52.220
AND THE ANSWER IS THEY'LL
JUST SAY THE TEXT OF THE FIRST

00:59:52.220 --> 00:59:55.850
AMENDMENT TELLS YOU THAT SPEECH
IS SUPPOSED TO BE PROTECTED AND

00:59:55.850 --> 00:59:58.711
IT DOESN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT WHO THE SPEAKER IS.

00:59:58.711 --> 01:00:01.210
BUT THIS IS ANOTHER EXAMPLE,
WELL FIRST OF ALL THE FACT THAT

01:00:01.210 --> 01:00:03.418
THE FIRST AMENDMENT TALKS
ABOUT THE FREEDOM OF SPEECH

01:00:03.418 --> 01:00:05.240
DOESN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT SPENDING MONEY.

01:00:05.240 --> 01:00:07.030
THE PEOPLE WHO WROTE
THE FIRST AMENDMENT

01:00:07.030 --> 01:00:09.490
HAD AN INCREDIBLY NARROW
UNDERSTANDING OF WHAT

01:00:09.490 --> 01:00:10.620
WAS PROTECTED.

01:00:10.620 --> 01:00:12.120
NONE OF THEM WOULD
HAVE DREAMED THAT

01:00:12.120 --> 01:00:15.590
THE IDEA OF SPENDING MONEY ON
ELECTIONS WAS PROTECTED SPEECH.

01:00:15.590 --> 01:00:17.620
WHEN CONGRESS PASSED
A SEDITION ACT

01:00:17.620 --> 01:00:19.760
IN THE FIRST DECADE OF
THE COUNTRY'S HISTORY,

01:00:19.760 --> 01:00:23.910
WHICH PUT PEOPLE IN JAIL FOR
CRITICIZING JOHN ADAMS TOO

01:00:23.910 --> 01:00:25.380
HARSHLY AS PRESIDENT.

01:00:25.380 --> 01:00:28.110
NOT A SINGLE FEDERAL JUDGE IN
THE COUNTRY THOUGHT THAT LAW

01:00:28.110 --> 01:00:31.320
WAS UNCONSTITUTIONAL BECAUSE
THEY HAD SUCH A NARROW

01:00:31.320 --> 01:00:32.660
VIEW OF THE FIRST AMENDMENT.

01:00:32.660 --> 01:00:35.120
BUT THE CONSERVATIVE JUSTICES
WON'T TALK ABOUT THE ORIGINAL

01:00:35.120 --> 01:00:37.203
UNDERSTANDING OF THE 1ST
AMENDMENT BECAUSE IT'S SO

01:00:37.203 --> 01:00:40.480
STRONGLY AGAINST THEIR POSITION,
THEY JUST SAY THAT WE WON'T GET

01:00:40.480 --> 01:00:42.930
TO THE ORIGINAL UNDERSTANDING,
BECAUSE THE FIRST AMENDMENT

01:00:42.930 --> 01:00:45.770
TALKS ABOUT SPEECH AND
SPENDING MONEY IS SPEECH.

01:00:45.770 --> 01:00:48.680
I THINK IT'S A LITTLE BIT
OUTRAGEOUS BECAUSE THEY'RE THE

01:00:48.680 --> 01:00:51.200
ONES THAT SAY WE OUGHT TO LOOK
AT ORIGINAL UNDERSTANDING AND

01:00:51.200 --> 01:00:52.990
THERE'S REALLY NOT A SHRED OF
EVIDENCE ON THEIR SIDE ON THAT

01:00:52.990 --> 01:00:53.210
ISSUE.

01:00:53.210 --> 01:00:53.710
[APPLAUSE]

01:00:53.710 --> 01:00:56.216
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL:
LAUREN, LINDA?

01:01:01.930 --> 01:01:06.430
&gt;&gt; LINDA GREENHOUSE: WELL YOUR
QUESTION ABOUT WHETHER ANY OF

01:01:06.430 --> 01:01:13.070
THE CURRENT CITIZENS UNITED
MAJORITY ARE ABOUT TO

01:01:13.070 --> 01:01:14.960
RECALIBRATE THEIR UNDERSTANDING.

01:01:14.960 --> 01:01:19.940
THEY HAD THAT CHANCE QUITE
SOON AFTER THE DECISION.

01:01:19.940 --> 01:01:24.360
A CASE CAME UP FROM MONTANA
WHERE THE MONTANA SUPREME COURT

01:01:24.360 --> 01:01:28.520
IN THE KIND OF DEFIANCE OF
CITIZENS UNITED HAD UPHELD

01:01:28.520 --> 01:01:34.120
STATE CORPORATE CAMPAIGN
SPENDING LIMITS UNDER THE STATE

01:01:34.120 --> 01:01:35.410
CONSTITUTION.

01:01:35.410 --> 01:01:38.830
AND MONTANA HAD A VERY
INTERESTING HISTORY WHERE

01:01:38.830 --> 01:01:41.880
CORPORATIONS HAD BASICALLY
BOUGHT U.S. SENATORS

01:01:41.880 --> 01:01:44.060
BACK IN THE DAY WHEN
SENATORS WERE APPOINTED BY

01:01:44.060 --> 01:01:45.090
STATE LEGISLATURES.

01:01:45.090 --> 01:01:49.410
SO THE MONTANA SUPREME COURT
SAID YOU KNOW WE'RE ACTING OUT

01:01:49.410 --> 01:01:51.270
OF OUR OWN SPECIAL HISTORY.

01:01:51.270 --> 01:01:52.360
AND WE HAVE THESE LAWS.

01:01:52.360 --> 01:01:54.610
AND WE THINK WE
CAN MAKE THE CASE

01:01:54.610 --> 01:01:57.520
THAT THE NOTION OF
CORRUPTION WHICH

01:01:57.520 --> 01:02:00.150
IS AT THE HEART OF CITIZENS
UNITED, A VERY NARROW VIEW.

01:02:00.150 --> 01:02:03.280
A QUID PRO QUO BASICALLY
BRIBERY, CORRUPTION.

01:02:03.280 --> 01:02:05.640
THAT WE UNDERSTAND CORRUPTION
MORE DEEPLY AND THIS

01:02:05.640 --> 01:02:08.300
IS WHAT WE THINK.

01:02:08.300 --> 01:02:11.320
THE COURT OVERTURNED IT
EVEN WITHOUT AN OPINION.

01:02:11.320 --> 01:02:14.900
OVERTURNED THE MONTANA
SUPREME COURT AND

01:02:14.900 --> 01:02:17.530
SAID THAT STATE LAW
WAS UNCONSTITUTIONAL.

01:02:17.530 --> 01:02:19.530
SO THAT WAS A CHANCE
TO EXPRESS A LITTLE

01:02:19.530 --> 01:02:20.750
BIT OF BUYER'S REMORSE.

01:02:20.750 --> 01:02:27.710
AND I DON'T SEE THAT ANYTHING
HAS COME THEIR WAY SINCE

01:02:27.710 --> 01:02:31.150
THAT'S GOING TO, IF ANYTHING,
THEY'RE DRILLING DOWN BECAUSE

01:02:31.150 --> 01:02:33.610
LAST TERM IN THE CASE
CALLED McCUTCHEON,

01:02:33.610 --> 01:02:38.260
THE CHEIF JUSTICE WROTE THE
MAJORITY OPINION ERASE THE

01:02:38.260 --> 01:02:43.800
LIMITS ON AGGREGATE INDIVIDUAL
POLITICAL CONTRIBUTIONS.

01:02:43.800 --> 01:02:47.480
IT SEEMS THAT EVERY TIME THEY
GET A NEW CHANCE WHERE THEY

01:02:47.480 --> 01:02:49.760
MIGHT PULL BACK A LITTLE,
INSTEAD THEY GO FURTHER.

01:02:49.760 --> 01:02:51.880
&gt;&gt; LAUREN SUDEALL LUCAS: AND
CORPORATIONS NOT ONLY HAVE FREE

01:02:51.880 --> 01:02:54.290
SPEECH RIGHTS, BUT THEY NOW
HAVE RELIGIOUS BELIEFS TOO.

01:02:54.290 --> 01:02:56.260
SO THEY'RE BECOMING MORE
AND MORE LIKE PEOPLE.

01:02:56.260 --> 01:03:01.220
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: OKAY.

01:03:01.220 --> 01:03:06.370
I THINK THAT TOOK CARE OF
CITIZENS UNITED. [LAUGHTER]

01:03:06.370 --> 01:03:09.650
THIS IS REALLY NOT ON POINT,
EXCEPT IT IS ON POINT.

01:03:09.650 --> 01:03:13.020
QUITE OFTEN WHEN I'VE HAD WITH
JUSTICE SCALIA ON THIS POINT HE

01:03:13.020 --> 01:03:15.080
SAYS I WOULD LIKE TO
SEE THE NEW YORK TIMES,

01:03:15.080 --> 01:03:18.327
KNOWING VERY WELL THAT I WAS
MARRIED TO SOMEONE WHO WROTE TO

01:03:18.327 --> 01:03:19.660
THE NEW YORK TIMES FOR 50 YEARS.

01:03:19.660 --> 01:03:23.080
HE SAID I'D LIKE TO SEE THE
NEW YORK TIMES SAYI THAT THEY

01:03:23.080 --> 01:03:29.130
DIDN'T HAVE THE FREE SPEECH
RIGHT TO CHARGE MONEY FOR THE

01:03:29.130 --> 01:03:31.940
THEIR EDITORIALS, WAS
ESSENTIALLY HIS POSITION.

01:03:31.940 --> 01:03:37.260
MY VIEW WAS THERE'S PROTECTION
OF THE PRESS, AS WELL.

01:03:37.260 --> 01:03:39.820
IT'S NEVER BEEN A VERY ENGAGED
DISCUSSION, I HAVE TO SAY.

01:03:39.820 --> 01:03:40.320
[LAUGHTER]

01:03:40.320 --> 01:03:46.140
I DO WANT TO SAY ONE
ADDITIONAL THING.

01:03:46.140 --> 01:03:48.880
ALMOST EVERYBODY WHO THINKS
ABOUT CITIZENS UNITED

01:03:48.880 --> 01:03:52.260
THINKS ABOUT IT FROM THE
CONTEXT OF THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH

01:03:52.260 --> 01:03:54.570
AND ESPECIALLY
CONGRESSIONAL RACES,

01:03:54.570 --> 01:03:56.920
OR LEGISLATIVE
RACES IN THE STATES.

01:03:56.920 --> 01:04:00.360
THERE ARE MANY STATES
THAT HAVE ELECTED JUDGES.

01:04:00.360 --> 01:04:01.950
37 STATES THAT HAVE
ELECTED JUDGES.

01:04:01.950 --> 01:04:04.950
AND CITIZENS UNITED
APPLIES TO THOSE, AS WELL.

01:04:04.950 --> 01:04:07.400
AND SOMETHING REALLY
TERRIBLE IS GOING ON

01:04:07.400 --> 01:04:10.250
IN OUR JUDICIAL SYSTEM
IN THE UNITED STATES.

01:04:10.250 --> 01:04:13.880
IT'S NOW COSTING HUGE AMOUNTS
OF MONEY IN SOME OF THOSE RACES.

01:04:13.880 --> 01:04:16.740
AND SOME OF THE BEST
JUDGES ARE SIMPLY NOT

01:04:16.740 --> 01:04:21.490
AGREEING TO BECOME JUDGES OR
STEPPING AWAY FROM THE COURT.

01:04:21.490 --> 01:04:28.190
MY MONTANA COLLEAGUES FELT VERY,
VERY STRONGLY ABOUT THAT CASE.

01:04:28.190 --> 01:04:32.200
AND I THINK IN MONTANA,
THERE MAY HAVE BEEN

01:04:32.200 --> 01:04:36.140
AN AMICUS BRIEF FILED BY FORMER
CHIEF JUSTICES OF THE MONTANA

01:04:36.140 --> 01:04:38.280
SUPREME COURT IN THAT CASE.

01:04:38.280 --> 01:04:41.110
THEY KNOW VERY
WELL WHAT HAPPENS.

01:04:41.110 --> 01:04:43.600
IT'S BAD ENOUGH PUTTING
MONEY INTO CONGRESSIONAL

01:04:43.600 --> 01:04:48.210
AND PRESIDENTIAL RACES,
BUT IT HAS A VERY POWERFUL,

01:04:48.210 --> 01:04:52.340
NEGATIVE IMPACT WHEN YOU PUT IT
INTO JUDICIAL RACES, AS WELL.

01:04:52.340 --> 01:04:54.780
THAT'S CERTAINLY
SOMETHING TO KEEP IN MIND.

01:04:54.780 --> 01:05:02.460
[APPLAUSE]

01:05:02.460 --> 01:05:11.280
PERHAPS AS A FINAL QUESTION
BEFORE WE TURN TO MICHAEL,

01:05:11.280 --> 01:05:15.170
THERE'S A MOVEMENT
UNDER WAY NOW KIND OF.

01:05:15.170 --> 01:05:19.070
LET'S SEE IF WE CAN PERSUADE
THEM TO HAVE NEW JUSTICES

01:05:19.070 --> 01:05:21.920
THAT ARE APPOINTED TO THE COURT
TO AGREE THAT THEY WILL STEP

01:05:21.920 --> 01:05:24.520
ASIDE AFTER A PARTICULAR
PERIOD OF TIME.

01:05:24.520 --> 01:05:28.180
IN OTHER WORDS IT GOES
TO THE LENGTH OF TENURE.

01:05:28.180 --> 01:05:31.410
FEDERAL JUDGES, AS YOU
KNOW, SERVE FOR LIFE.

01:05:31.410 --> 01:05:33.860
AT THE TIME THE
CONSTITUTION WAS WRITTEN.

01:05:33.860 --> 01:05:37.890
THE APPROXIMATE
LIFE SPAN WAS 50.

01:05:37.890 --> 01:05:41.710
SO MANY OF US ARE VERY HAPPY
THAT THERE'S BEEN MEDICAL

01:05:41.710 --> 01:05:44.310
PROGRESS SINCE THAT TIME.

01:05:44.310 --> 01:05:47.300
BUT IT HAS MEANT
THAT OUR JUSTICES ARE

01:05:47.300 --> 01:05:51.510
SERVING FOR LONGER AND LONGER
AND LONGER PERIODS OF TIME.

01:05:51.510 --> 01:05:54.430
THAT IS TRUE BY THE WAY FOR
THE ENTIRE FEDERAL SYSTEM,

01:05:54.430 --> 01:05:57.400
NOT JUST FOR THE NINE JUSTICES
ON THE UNITED STATES SUPREME

01:05:57.400 --> 01:05:57.900
COURT.

01:05:57.900 --> 01:06:01.830
BUT CONGRESS HAS CREATED
A MECHANISM WHICH MAKES IT

01:06:01.830 --> 01:06:05.590
POSSIBLE FOR FEDERAL JUDGES
ON THE CIRCUIT COURTS AND THE

01:06:05.590 --> 01:06:08.720
DISTRICT COURTS TO TAKE
WHAT'S CALLED SENIOR STATUS.

01:06:08.720 --> 01:06:12.300
IT'S A LITTLE BIT ABOUT WHAT
WE DO AT UNIVERSITIES NOW AFTER

01:06:12.300 --> 01:06:16.680
THEY PUT AN END TO 70 YEARS
A MANDATORY AGE RETIREMENT,

01:06:16.680 --> 01:06:21.260
WHERE YOU CAN REMAIN FULL TIME
ACTING JUDGE OR PART TIME.

01:06:21.260 --> 01:06:24.020
BUT YOU AUTOMATICALLY GET
ANOTHER JUDICIAL POSITION IN

01:06:24.020 --> 01:06:26.720
YOUR COURT, THAT OF COURSE WE
CAN'T DO IN THE UNITED STATES

01:06:26.720 --> 01:06:29.840
SUPREME COURT, BECAUSE WE
HAVE THE NINE JUSTICES.

01:06:29.840 --> 01:06:32.820
ANY VIEWS FROM ANY OF
YOU ABOUT WHETHER THAT'S

01:06:32.820 --> 01:06:35.490
A GOOD OR BAD IDEA AND
WHAT'S THE LIKELIHOOD OF IT

01:06:35.490 --> 01:06:36.690
SUCCEEDING?

01:06:36.690 --> 01:06:39.559
AND MICHAEL, YOU
NEED NOT ANSWER,

01:06:39.559 --> 01:06:41.350
BECAUSE YOUR JUSTICE
IS SITTING RIGHT HERE.

01:06:41.350 --> 01:06:43.160
OR MAYBE YOU HAVE
A VERY STRONG VIEW.

01:06:43.160 --> 01:06:43.660
[LAUGHTER]

01:06:43.660 --> 01:06:47.200
&gt;&gt; MICHAEL KLARMAN: I HAD A
COUPLE STUDENTS WHO WROTE A

01:06:47.200 --> 01:06:50.490
NOTE YEARS AGO AND THEIR
PROPOSAL WAS LIMITED TO THE

01:06:50.490 --> 01:06:54.480
SUPREME COURT, BUT IT WOULD
BE 18 YEAR STAGGERED TERMS.

01:06:54.480 --> 01:06:56.230
AND I THOUGHT IT WAS
A BRILLIANT PROPOSAL.

01:06:56.230 --> 01:06:58.313
I DON'T THINK IT HAS ANY
PRACTICAL CHANCE OF BEING

01:06:58.313 --> 01:07:01.060
ADOPTED, BUT IT WAS BRILLIANT
PROPOSAL BECAUSE IT SOLVES ALL

01:07:01.060 --> 01:07:03.780
OF THE PROBLEMS THAT EXIST
WITH THE CURRENT SYSTEMS.

01:07:03.780 --> 01:07:06.150
SO THERE'S A PROBLEM WITH
STRATEGIC APPOINTMENTS.

01:07:06.150 --> 01:07:08.350
PRESIDENTS WILL APPOINT
PEOPLE YOUNGER AND YOUNGER,

01:07:08.350 --> 01:07:11.000
BECAUSE THEY UNDERSTAND IT'S
IMPORTANT TO HAVE A PARTICULAR

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:13.260
VIEW REPRESENTED
AS LONG AS YOU CAN.

01:07:13.260 --> 01:07:14.920
THERE ARE STRATEGIC RETIREMENTS.

01:07:14.920 --> 01:07:16.760
JUSTICES WILL LEAVE
THE COURT WHEN

01:07:16.760 --> 01:07:20.070
THERE'S A PRESIDENT SITTING WHO
THEY BELIEVE ROUGHLY REPRESENTS

01:07:20.070 --> 01:07:22.240
THE VIEWS THEY WANT
WRITTEN INTO LAW.

01:07:22.240 --> 01:07:24.000
THERE'S THE PROBLEM OF FORTUITY.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:26.480
WILLIAM HOWARD TAFT
HAD 5 OR 6 APPOINTMENTS

01:07:26.480 --> 01:07:27.730
IN ONE 4 YEAR PERIOD.

01:07:27.730 --> 01:07:32.180
JIMMY CARTER HAD NONE DURING
HIS 4 YEAR TERN IN OFFICE.

01:07:32.180 --> 01:07:34.165
AND IT'S A MANDATORY
RETIREMENT, WHICH

01:07:34.165 --> 01:07:36.540
WE HAVE IN MOST AREAS OF LIFE,
AND IT SEEMS LIKE IT WOULD

01:07:36.540 --> 01:07:38.498
PROBABLY BE A PRETTY GOOD
IDEA IN THAT CONTEXT.

01:07:38.498 --> 01:07:40.000
&gt;&gt; NOT IN ACADEMIA, MICHAEL.

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:40.500
[LAUGHTER]

01:07:40.500 --> 01:07:44.970
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: I THINK
I CAN SPEAK FOR MICHAEL.

01:07:44.970 --> 01:07:47.730
YOU WOULD SUPPORT MANDATORY
RETIREMENT FOR PROFESSORS.

01:07:47.730 --> 01:07:49.970
&gt;&gt; MICHAEL KLARMAN: I WOULD.

01:07:49.970 --> 01:07:55.900
&gt;&gt; LINDA GREENHOUSE: I
THINK THE 18 YEAR TERM.

01:07:55.900 --> 01:07:58.790
I THINK I READ
THAT STUDENT NOTE.

01:07:58.790 --> 01:08:03.280
IT'S WORTH DISCUSSING FOR THE
REASONS THAT MICHAEL SAID.

01:08:03.280 --> 01:08:06.610
THE NOTION THAT SUPREME COURT
NOMINEES SHOULD VOLUNTARILY

01:08:06.610 --> 01:08:09.365
PLEDGE THAT THEY WOULD DO IT
STRIKES ME AS KIND OF NUTTY.

01:08:14.020 --> 01:08:18.740
IT'S INTERESTING THAT DEMOCRACY,
OR WHAT PASSES AS DEMOCRACY

01:08:18.740 --> 01:08:21.069
HAS SPREAD AROUND THE WORLD
AND DIFFERENT COUNTRIES

01:08:21.069 --> 01:08:23.970
HAVE ADOPTED ASPECTS
OF OUR SYSTEM,

01:08:23.970 --> 01:08:26.609
INCLUDING CONSTITUTIONAL COURTS.

01:08:26.609 --> 01:08:30.200
NOT A SINGLE COUNTRY
HAS ADOPTED LIFE TENURE.

01:08:30.200 --> 01:08:34.899
THEY EITHER HAVE AGE LIMITS,
THEY HAVE TERM LIMITS.

01:08:34.899 --> 01:08:37.890
OF THE 50 STATES,
ONLY RHODE ISLAND

01:08:37.890 --> 01:08:39.710
HAS LIFE TENURE FOR ITS JUDGES.

01:08:39.710 --> 01:08:44.460
EVERY OTHER STATE HAS EITHER
TERM LIMIT OR AGE LIMITS.

01:08:44.460 --> 01:08:47.950
SO THESE SYSTEMS ARE
VOTING WITH THEIR FEET THAT

01:08:47.950 --> 01:08:51.700
THERE IS SOMETHING A LITTLE
PROBLEMATIC ABOUT IT.

01:08:51.700 --> 01:08:59.430
AND IT CERTAINLY DOES ELEVATE
THE KIND OF DRAMA AROUND ANY

01:08:59.430 --> 01:09:03.560
SUPREME COURT VACANCY BECAUSE
YOU'RE LOOKING OUT AT SUCH A

01:09:03.560 --> 01:09:05.990
LONG TIMELINE.

01:09:05.990 --> 01:09:11.330
AND AS MICHAEL SAID, JUSTICES
ARE GETTING APPOINTED AT

01:09:11.330 --> 01:09:12.420
YOUNGER AND YOUNGER AGES.

01:09:12.420 --> 01:09:16.380
JOHN ROBERTS AT 50 WAS
THE YOUNGEST CHIEF JUSTICE

01:09:16.380 --> 01:09:18.770
TO BE APPOINTED
SINCE JOHN MARSHALL.

01:09:18.770 --> 01:09:22.090
SO THERE'S STUFF TO
DISCUSS ABOUT THIS.

01:09:22.090 --> 01:09:26.109
IT'S A WORTHWHILE CONVERSATION,
BUT IT'S A VERY LONG TERM ONE.

01:09:26.109 --> 01:09:28.920
AND EXTRACTING PROMISES FROM
NOMINEES IS NOT THE ANSWER,

01:09:28.920 --> 01:09:30.630
I'M PRETTY SURE OF THAT.

01:09:30.630 --> 01:09:33.849
&gt;&gt; LAUREN SUDEALL LUCAS: I WOULD
JUST ADD THAT I DON'T KNOW IF

01:09:33.849 --> 01:09:35.890
IMPLEMENTING THESE TYPES
OF PROPOSALS WOULD HELP.

01:09:35.890 --> 01:09:38.620
BUT I THINK THERE'S A REAL
NEED AND PERHAPS HAVING MORE

01:09:38.620 --> 01:09:40.010
FREQUENT TURNOVER
WOULD HELP WITH

01:09:40.010 --> 01:09:44.160
THIS, HAVING A DIVERSITY OF
EXPERIENCE NOT JUST TALK ABOUT

01:09:44.160 --> 01:09:47.120
DIVERSITY OF RACE AND GENDER
IN TERMS OF WHO'S ON THE COURT.

01:09:47.120 --> 01:09:50.359
BUT ALSO DIVERSITY OF EXPERIENCE
AND HAVING A RELATIVELY RECENT

01:09:50.359 --> 01:09:52.140
EXPERIENCE WITH HOW
CASES ARE LITIGATED

01:09:52.140 --> 01:09:54.540
IN PRACTICE, PARTICULARLY IN
OTHER PARTS OF THE COUNTRY.

01:09:54.540 --> 01:09:57.250
I LIVE IN A STATE WHERE PEOPLE
ARE ROUTINELY UNREPRESENTED BY

01:09:57.250 --> 01:09:58.180
COUNSEL.

01:09:58.180 --> 01:10:00.300
THE CASES ARE RESOLVED
WITHOUT A DEFENDANT EVEN

01:10:00.300 --> 01:10:02.160
SPEAKING TO A LAWYER.

01:10:02.160 --> 01:10:04.160
AND PEOPLE WHO HAVE
PROSECUTORIAL EXPERIENCE,

01:10:04.160 --> 01:10:06.660
OR PUBLIC DEFENDER EXPERIENCE
AND ACTUALLY KNOWING HOW THESE

01:10:06.660 --> 01:10:09.720
THINGS WORK ON THE GROUND AND
PRACTICE OBSERVING INTERACTIONS

01:10:09.720 --> 01:10:12.330
BETWEEN CITIZENS AND
POLICE WOULD REALLY HELP

01:10:12.330 --> 01:10:15.020
WITH HELPING THE COURT GRAPPLE
WITH THESE ISSUES AS THEY TRY

01:10:15.020 --> 01:10:15.120
TO DECIDE HOW TO DEAL
WITH IT AT THIS LEVEL,

01:10:15.120 --> 01:10:16.200
IT WOULD BE HELPFUL TO
UNDERSTAND HOW THINGS

01:10:16.200 --> 01:10:17.600
OPERATE ON THE GROUND.

01:10:17.600 --> 01:10:18.100
[APPLAUSE]

01:10:18.100 --> 01:10:21.530
&gt;&gt; MARGARET MARSHALL: I
WOULD ADD ONE LAST THING.

01:10:21.530 --> 01:10:24.190
I THINK I'M CORRECT,
MAYBE I'M NOT.

01:10:24.190 --> 01:10:28.050
BUT I THINK THIS IS THE FIRST
COURT EVER WHERE THERE'S BEEN

01:10:28.050 --> 01:10:30.130
NOBODY WITH ANY
STATE EXPERIENCE.

01:10:30.130 --> 01:10:31.960
AND I DON'T MEAN
JUST STATE, JUDICIAL.

01:10:31.960 --> 01:10:34.650
BUT JUSTICE SOUTER HAD OF
COURSE BEEN A STATE COURT JUDGE,

01:10:34.650 --> 01:10:37.750
AND CHIEF JUSTICE
WARREN, GOVERNOR.

01:10:37.750 --> 01:10:39.180
PEOPLE HAVE HAD
STATE EXPERIENCE.

01:10:39.180 --> 01:10:41.880
I THINK IT'S ALSO IMPORTANT THAT
WE ARE BECOMING AN INCREASINGLY

01:10:41.880 --> 01:10:43.771
FEDERALIZED COURT.

01:10:43.771 --> 01:10:46.270
MICHAEL, I DON'T KNOW IF IT WAS
YOU OR JOHN WHO TOLD ME THIS

01:10:46.270 --> 01:10:51.160
YEAR THE COURT HAS TAKEN A VERY
FEW NUMBER OF CASES FROM STATE

01:10:51.160 --> 01:10:51.700
COURTS.

01:10:51.700 --> 01:10:55.280
AND THAT'S WHERE MOST OF
THE JUSTICE GETS DONE.

01:10:55.280 --> 01:10:58.820
I FOR ONE HAVE A PROPOSAL
THAT IF WE HAVE LIMITED

01:10:58.820 --> 01:11:03.470
TENURE, EITHER BY
AGE LIMITATION, OR BY

01:11:03.470 --> 01:11:06.990
NUMBERS OF YEARS SERVED, THAT
IT NOT BE IMPLEMENTED UNTIL

01:11:06.990 --> 01:11:10.500
AFTER THE LAST SITTING JUDGE
HAS NO LONGER APPLIED TO THEM,

01:11:10.500 --> 01:11:12.930
BECAUSE I THINK IT'S VERY
PROBLEMATIC WHEN YOU TRY

01:11:12.930 --> 01:11:15.500
TO DO IT WITH A SITTING COURT.

01:11:15.500 --> 01:11:19.100
AND IN ANY EVENT, I WOULD
LIKE TO THANK JOHN ADAMS

01:11:19.100 --> 01:11:22.300
IN THE MASSACHUSETTS
CONSTITUTION FOR TELLING US

01:11:22.300 --> 01:11:23.930
THAT WE HAD LIFETIME TENURE.

01:11:23.930 --> 01:11:26.060
BECAUSE IF WE DIDN'T,
WE WOULDN'T HAVE THIS

01:11:26.060 --> 01:11:28.510
EXTRAORDINARY,
BRILLIANT, WONDERFUL,

01:11:28.510 --> 01:11:45.580
AMAZING WOMAN THAT WE HAVE
TO CELEBRATE HERE TODAY.

01:11:45.580 --> 01:11:47.390
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

01:11:47.390 --> 01:11:51.990
SO IF YOU ARE A
LAWYER, ESPECIALLY ONE

01:11:51.990 --> 01:11:54.260
WHO'S JUST BEGINNING
THEIR CAREER, WHAT

01:11:54.260 --> 01:11:59.480
IS THE VERY, VERY, VERY
BEST JOB IN THE WORLD

01:11:59.480 --> 01:12:02.940
THAT YOU COULD POSSIBLY HAVE?

01:12:02.940 --> 01:12:07.010
IT IS NO DOUBT TO BE A LAW
CLERK FOR JUSTICE RUTH BADER

01:12:07.010 --> 01:12:08.920
GINSBURG.

01:12:08.920 --> 01:12:12.500
AND MICHAEL KLARMAN IS
GOING TO GIVE US A LITTLE

01:12:12.500 --> 01:12:16.720
PERSPECTIVE OF WHAT IT IS
LIKE TO HAVE THAT BEAUTIFUL

01:12:16.720 --> 01:12:17.390
POSITION.

01:12:17.390 --> 01:12:20.190
MICHAEL?

01:12:20.190 --> 01:12:23.020
[APPLAUSE]

01:12:23.020 --> 01:12:28.910
&gt;&gt; MICHAEL KLARMAN: THANK YOU.

01:12:28.910 --> 01:12:31.840
WHEN PRESIDENT CLINTON
NOMINATED RUTH BADER GINSBURG

01:12:31.840 --> 01:12:35.250
TO THE SUPREME COURT
IN 1993, HE SAID

01:12:35.250 --> 01:12:37.260
QUOTE MANY ADMIRERS
OF HER WORK SAID

01:12:37.260 --> 01:12:40.170
THAT SHE IS TO THE WOMEN'S
MOVEMENT WHAT FORMER SUPREME

01:12:40.170 --> 01:12:41.950
COURT JUSTICE
THURGOOD MARSHALL WAS

01:12:41.950 --> 01:12:44.770
TO MOVEMENT OF THE RIGHTS
OF AFRICAN AMERICANS.

01:12:44.770 --> 01:12:47.010
CLINTON WHO WAS A GRADUATE
OF A LAW SCHOOL OTHER

01:12:47.010 --> 01:12:50.070
THAN HARVARD THAT SHALL NOT BE
NAMED, EXPLAINED THAT HE COULD

01:12:50.070 --> 01:12:52.690
THINK OF NO GREATER
COMPLIMENT TO BESTOW ON

01:12:52.690 --> 01:12:54.200
AN AMERICAN LAWYER.

01:12:54.200 --> 01:12:56.850
INDEED JUSTICE GINSBURG
IS ONE OF THE FEW JUSTICES

01:12:56.850 --> 01:13:00.430
IN AMERICAN HISTORY WHO WOULD
BE A DESERVED FAMOUS AMERICAN IF

01:13:00.430 --> 01:13:03.580
SHE HAD NEVER SERVED
ON THE SUPREME COURT.

01:13:03.580 --> 01:13:06.300
I AM GOING TO TELL YOU A FEW
STORIES ABOUT JUSTICE GINSBURG

01:13:06.300 --> 01:13:10.780
AND HER BIOGRAPHY AND HER
ROLE AS A TRAILBLAZING

01:13:10.780 --> 01:13:13.300
LITIGATOR FOR SOCIAL REFORM.

01:13:13.300 --> 01:13:15.210
AS MARGIE SAID, I HAD
THE GOOD FORTUNATE TO

01:13:15.210 --> 01:13:16.630
CLERK FOR HER 30 YEARS AGO.

01:13:16.630 --> 01:13:20.450
SO I KNOW SOME OF THESE STORIES
AS A RESULT OF HAVING WRITTEN

01:13:20.450 --> 01:13:22.200
SOME ABOUT HER IN THE PAST.

01:13:22.200 --> 01:13:24.320
GINSBURG'S PERSONAL
STORY ILLUSTRATES

01:13:24.320 --> 01:13:27.800
WHAT THE PROFESSIONAL WORLD WAS
LIKE FOR WOMEN HALF A CENTURY

01:13:27.800 --> 01:13:28.580
AGO.

01:13:28.580 --> 01:13:31.790
HOW MUCH IT'S CHANGED SINCE
THEN, AND HOW THE EFFORTS

01:13:31.790 --> 01:13:34.970
OF A TALENTED AND HARD
WORKING LAWYER CAN CONTRIBUTE

01:13:34.970 --> 01:13:37.210
TO PROGRESSIVE SOCIAL REFORM.

01:13:37.210 --> 01:13:40.890
WHEN GINSBURG ENTERED
HARVARD LAW SCHOOL IN 1956,

01:13:40.890 --> 01:13:45.400
SHE WAS ONE OF ONLY NINE
WOMEN IN A CLASS OF OVER 500.

01:13:45.400 --> 01:13:48.220
HARVARD LAW SCHOOL HAD NOT
ADMITTED WOMAN AT ALL UNTIL

01:13:48.220 --> 01:13:49.510
1950.

01:13:49.510 --> 01:13:53.640
AT THE TIME THAT GINSBURG WAS
MATRICULATED AT HLS, WOMEN WERE

01:13:53.640 --> 01:13:56.160
NOT PERMITTED TO LIVE IN
LAW SCHOOL DORMITORIES,

01:13:56.160 --> 01:13:58.950
AND THEY WERE DENIED
ACCESS TO DINING TABLES

01:13:58.950 --> 01:14:00.610
AT THE FACULTY CLUB.

01:14:00.610 --> 01:14:03.470
AND THE ANNUAL LAW
REVIEW BANQUET ENCOURAGED

01:14:03.470 --> 01:14:07.190
MEMBERS TO BRING WITH THEM THEIR
FATHERS, BUT NOT THEIR MOTHERS

01:14:07.190 --> 01:14:08.910
OR THEIR WIVES.

01:14:08.910 --> 01:14:12.200
EARLY IN THE SCHOOL YEAR THE LAW
SCHOOL'S DEAN INVITED THE NINE

01:14:12.200 --> 01:14:15.040
WOMEN IN THE CLASS TO HIS
HOUSE FOR DINNER AND DURING THE

01:14:15.040 --> 01:14:17.060
COURSE OF THE
EVENING'S CONVERSATION,

01:14:17.060 --> 01:14:20.740
HE ASKED THEM WHY THEY WANTED
TO ATTEND HARVARD LAW SCHOOL,

01:14:20.740 --> 01:14:23.880
TAKING UP A SPACE THAT A MAN
COULD PRESUMEDLY PUT TO BETTER

01:14:23.880 --> 01:14:25.020
USE.

01:14:25.020 --> 01:14:28.590
GINS BURG REPORTS BEING
UNPREPARED FOR THE QUESTION.

01:14:28.590 --> 01:14:31.070
NOW AS YOU MAY KNOW HER
SPOUSE, MARTY GINSBURG

01:14:31.070 --> 01:14:33.700
WAS A YEAR AHEAD OF HER
AT HARVARD LAW SCHOOL.

01:14:33.700 --> 01:14:36.920
AND AS SHE LATER RECOUNTS
HER REJOINDER TO THE DEAN,

01:14:36.920 --> 01:14:39.660
ALL I COULD THINK TO
SAY WAS THAT MY HUSBAND

01:14:39.660 --> 01:14:42.460
WAS IN THE SECOND YEAR
CLASS, AND IT WAS IMPORTANT

01:14:42.460 --> 01:14:45.080
FOR A WIFE TO UNDERSTAND
HER HUSBAND'S WORK.

01:14:45.080 --> 01:14:47.840
[LAUGHTER]

01:14:47.840 --> 01:14:50.650
FEW PEOPLE AT THAT POINT COULD
HAVE CONFIDENTLY PREDICTED

01:14:50.650 --> 01:14:53.460
THERE WOULD EVER BE A WOMAN ON
THE UNITED STATES SUPREME COURT

01:14:53.460 --> 01:14:56.740
AND INDEED THERE WAS NOT
FOR ANOTHER 25 YEARS.

01:14:56.740 --> 01:15:00.460
GINSBURG TRANSFERRED TO COLUMBIA
LAW SCHOOL AFTER TWO YEARS AT

01:15:00.460 --> 01:15:02.700
HARVARD WHEN MARTY
GRADUATED AND TOOK

01:15:02.700 --> 01:15:04.640
A JOB WITH A NEW YORK LAW FIRM.

01:15:04.640 --> 01:15:07.030
THEY WERE RAISING A YOUNG
DAUGHTER AT THE TIME.

01:15:07.030 --> 01:15:09.510
GINSBURG GRADUATED IN 1959.

01:15:09.510 --> 01:15:12.210
SHE WAS TIED FOR FIRST
IN HER CLASS AT COLUMBIA,

01:15:12.210 --> 01:15:15.160
AND SHE HAD BEEN ON THE LAW
REVIEW BOTH AT COLUMBIA AND AT

01:15:15.160 --> 01:15:16.060
HARVARD.

01:15:16.060 --> 01:15:19.440
YET HER PROFESSORS HAD
TROUBLE FINDING HER A FEDERAL

01:15:19.440 --> 01:15:23.140
CLERK COURTSHIP, EVEN THOUGH SHE
WAS EMINENTLY QUALIFIED FOR IT.

01:15:23.140 --> 01:15:25.360
NO FEDERAL JUDGE IN
THE NEW YORK CITY AREA

01:15:25.360 --> 01:15:28.650
WOULD HIRE A YOUNG
MOTHER AS A LAW CLERK.

01:15:28.650 --> 01:15:31.270
FINALLY ONE OF HER
PROFESSORS, GERALD GUNTHER,

01:15:31.270 --> 01:15:34.180
PREVAILED UPON A FEDERAL
DISTRICT COURT JUDGE EDMOND

01:15:34.180 --> 01:15:38.970
PALMIERI TO HIRE GINSBURG BY
OFFERING A PERSONAL GUARANTEE

01:15:38.970 --> 01:15:43.930
THAT IF SHE DID NOT WORK OUT HE
WOULD FIND A MALE REPLACEMENT.

01:15:43.930 --> 01:15:47.200
SHE WORKED OUT SO WELL THAT IN
THE FUTURE PALMIERI COULD NOT

01:15:47.200 --> 01:15:49.660
GET ENOUGH FEMALE CLERKS.

01:15:49.660 --> 01:15:51.460
AS MOST OF YOU KNOW
JUSTICE GINSBURG

01:15:51.460 --> 01:15:54.040
WAS THE LEADING WOMENS RIGHTS
LAWYER IN THE UNITED STATES

01:15:54.040 --> 01:15:55.450
IN THE 1970S.

01:15:55.450 --> 01:15:58.800
SHE ARGUED 6 LANDMARK CASES
IN THE UNITED STATES SUPREME

01:15:58.800 --> 01:16:01.070
COURT, WINNING 5 OF THEM.

01:16:01.070 --> 01:16:04.150
NOW ONE FAIRLY UNIQUE
OBSTACLE CONFRONTED BY LAWYERS

01:16:04.150 --> 01:16:06.880
FOR SOCIAL REFORM IS EVEN
HAVING THEIR ARGUMENTS TAKEN

01:16:06.880 --> 01:16:08.090
SERIOUSLY.

01:16:08.090 --> 01:16:11.100
IN 1938 CHARLES
HAMILTON HOUSTON,

01:16:11.100 --> 01:16:12.970
ONE OF THE LEADING
BLACK CIVIL RIGHTS

01:16:12.970 --> 01:16:16.230
LITIGATORS IN THE COUNTRY AND A
GRADUATE OF HARVARD LAW SCHOOL

01:16:16.230 --> 01:16:19.200
LITERALLY HAD ONE OF THE
JUSTICES TURN HIS BACK

01:16:19.200 --> 01:16:22.240
ON HIM IN DURING ORAL
ARGUMENT IN A LANDMARK RACE

01:16:22.240 --> 01:16:24.680
DISCRIMINATION CASE
IN ORDER TO INDICATE

01:16:24.680 --> 01:16:27.580
HIS PROFOUND DISRESPECT
FOR A BLACK MAN.

01:16:27.580 --> 01:16:30.780
40 YEARS LATER, ORAL ADVOCATE
RUTH BADER GINSBURG HAD TO

01:16:30.780 --> 01:16:33.620
CONFRONT CONDESCENDING
HUMOR FROM THE BENCH AS SHE

01:16:33.620 --> 01:16:35.850
CHALLENGED THE EXCLUSION
OF WOMEN FROM JURIES

01:16:35.850 --> 01:16:37.350
IN THE STATE OF MISSOURI.

01:16:37.350 --> 01:16:40.010
AFTER GINSBURG HAS
CONCLUDED HER ORAL ARGUMENT

01:16:40.010 --> 01:16:43.450
IN THE CASE, ONE OF THE JUSTICES
LEANED OVER FROM THE BENCH TO

01:16:43.450 --> 01:16:45.670
ASK ONE FINAL QUESTION.

01:16:45.670 --> 01:16:47.750
YOU WON'T SETTLE
FOR PUTTING SUSAN B.

01:16:47.750 --> 01:16:50.300
ANTHONY ON THE DOLLAR
THEN I TAKE IT?

01:16:50.300 --> 01:16:53.600
IN ANOTHER LANDMARK CASE ONE
OF THE JUSTICES PRIVATELY

01:16:53.600 --> 01:16:56.440
CRITISIZED GINSBURG'S
BRIEF AS BEING EMOTIONAL,

01:16:56.440 --> 01:17:00.560
INVOKING ONE OF THE TRADITIONAL
GENDER PUTDOWNS OF THE ERA.

01:17:00.560 --> 01:17:03.300
IN ADDITION TO THE CHALLENGE
OF BEING TAKEN SERIOUSLY,

01:17:03.300 --> 01:17:06.150
ONE OF THE PRINCIPLE
DIFFICULTIES THAT SOCIAL REFORM

01:17:06.150 --> 01:17:09.040
LITIGATORS FACE IS
CONVINCING JUSTICES

01:17:09.040 --> 01:17:12.680
OF THE UNFAIRNESS OF A SYSTEM,
UNDER WHICH THEY THEMSELVES HAD

01:17:12.680 --> 01:17:15.030
BENEFITED AND WHICH
HAD BECOME GROUNDED

01:17:15.030 --> 01:17:19.690
IN AN IDEOLOGY SO PERVASIVE THAT
THEY HAD TROUBLE EVEN NOTICING

01:17:19.690 --> 01:17:22.080
THAT IT'S ASSUMPTIONS
ARE CONTROVERSIAL.

01:17:22.080 --> 01:17:24.990
GINSBURG CONFRONTED
EXACTLY THAT PROBLEM TRYING

01:17:24.990 --> 01:17:28.530
TO CONVINCE ELDERLY MALE
JUSTICES IN THE 1970S

01:17:28.530 --> 01:17:32.980
OF THE INSIDIOUS CONSEQUENCES
OF SEX CLASSIFICATIONS.

01:17:32.980 --> 01:17:36.040
VIRTUALLY ALL SEX
CLASSIFICATIONS ARE AS JUSTICE

01:17:36.040 --> 01:17:39.660
GINSBURG LIKES TO SAY
A DOUBLE EDGED SWORD.

01:17:39.660 --> 01:17:43.350
MANY SUCH STATUTES TANGIBLY
DISADVANTAGE MALES AND NOT

01:17:43.350 --> 01:17:47.530
FEMALES, THAT THEY INTANGIBLY
HARM WOMEN BY PERPETUATING

01:17:47.530 --> 01:17:50.570
STEREOTYPES OF FEMALE
DEPENDENCY, PASSIVITY,

01:17:50.570 --> 01:17:52.680
AND LACK OF BUSINESS ABILITY.

01:17:52.680 --> 01:17:56.940
GINSBURG NEEDED TO CONVINCE
THESE JUSTICES THAT WOMEN WERE

01:17:56.940 --> 01:18:01.090
HARMED FOR EXAMPLE BY STATUTES
THAT REQUIRED MEN BUT NOT

01:18:01.090 --> 01:18:04.960
WOMEN TO PAY ALIMONY OR THAT
PERMITTED WOMEN, BUT NOT MEN

01:18:04.960 --> 01:18:07.380
THE CHOICE OF WHETHER
TO SERVE ON A JURY.

01:18:07.380 --> 01:18:10.330
IN A TELLING CONVERSATION WITH
HARVARD LAW SCHOOL STUDENTS

01:18:10.330 --> 01:18:14.670
EARLY IN 1973, ONE OF THE MALE
JUSTICES AND THERE WERE ONLY

01:18:14.670 --> 01:18:18.820
MALE JUSTICES IN 1973
EXPRESSED BEWILDERMENT AS TO

01:18:18.820 --> 01:18:21.800
WHY WOMEN WANTED AN
EQUAL RIGHTS AMENDMENT.

01:18:21.800 --> 01:18:24.700
IN HIS VIEW, THE
FEMALE OF THE SPECIES

01:18:24.700 --> 01:18:26.560
HAS THE BEST OF BOTH WORLDS.

01:18:26.560 --> 01:18:29.110
SHE CAN ATTACK LAWS THAT
UNREASONABLY DISCRIMINATE

01:18:29.110 --> 01:18:32.890
AGAINST HER, WHILE PRESERVING
THOSE THAT FAVOR HER.

01:18:32.890 --> 01:18:35.020
GINSBURG REPORTED
BEING DEPRESSED

01:18:35.020 --> 01:18:37.420
WHEN SHE HEARD THE
ACCOUNT OF THAT SPEECH.

01:18:37.420 --> 01:18:39.880
A LENGTHY EXCHANGE
BETWEEN GINSBURG AND TWO

01:18:39.880 --> 01:18:42.010
OF THE JUSTICES
AT ORAL ARGUMENT,

01:18:42.010 --> 01:18:47.300
IN THE CASE OF CALIFANO V.
GOLDFARB IN 1976 REVEALS HOW

01:18:47.300 --> 01:18:51.550
DIFFICULT IT WAS TO CONVINCE
ELDERLY MALE JUSTICES THAT ALL

01:18:51.550 --> 01:18:55.490
SEX CLASSIFICATIONS ADVERSELY
AFFECTED WOMEN BECAUSE

01:18:55.490 --> 01:18:57.910
OF THIS DOUBLE EDGED NATURE.

01:18:57.910 --> 01:18:59.670
THE SOCIAL SECURITY
PROVISION THAT

01:18:59.670 --> 01:19:03.040
WAS AT ISSUE IN GOLDFARB
AUTOMATICALLY PROVIDED

01:19:03.040 --> 01:19:06.530
SURVIVORS BENEFITS FOR
THE WIDOWS OF COVERED MALE

01:19:06.530 --> 01:19:09.440
EMPLOYEES, BUT REQUIRED
THAT THE WIDOWERS

01:19:09.440 --> 01:19:13.120
OF COVERED FEMALE EMPLOYEES
DEMONSTRATE ACTUAL

01:19:13.120 --> 01:19:15.960
ECONOMIC DEPENDENCY
ON THEIR SPOUSES.

01:19:15.960 --> 01:19:19.400
TO GINSBURG SUCH A PROVISION
HAD THREE DIFFERENT FLAWS.

01:19:19.400 --> 01:19:22.600
FIRST OF ALL IT DISCRIMINATED
AGAINST FEMALE WAGE EARNERS,

01:19:22.600 --> 01:19:25.600
SECOND IT DISCRIMINATED
AGAINST THE MALE BENEFICIARIES,

01:19:25.600 --> 01:19:29.680
AND THIRD IT PROPETUATED THE
PERFIDIOUS SEX STEREOTYPE THAT

01:19:29.680 --> 01:19:32.860
MALES WERE PRIMARILY BREAD
WINNERS AND WOMEN WERE

01:19:32.860 --> 01:19:34.610
PREDOMINANTLY HOMEMAKERS.

01:19:34.610 --> 01:19:38.040
SOME OF THE JUSTICES HAD
DIFFICULTY SEEING THESE POINTS.

01:19:38.040 --> 01:19:39.840
THE FIRST QUESTION
THAT WAS DIRECTED

01:19:39.840 --> 01:19:43.020
TO GINSBURG FROM THE BENCH WAS
WHETHER THE PROVISION AT ISSUE

01:19:43.020 --> 01:19:45.940
DISCRIMINATED AGAINST
MALES OR FEMALES,

01:19:45.940 --> 01:19:49.540
WHETHER IT COULD NOT BE CAST
IN EITHER WAY, AND WHY SHE HAD

01:19:49.540 --> 01:19:52.890
CHOSEN TO TREAT IT AS AN
ANTI FEMALE DISCRIMINATION.

01:19:52.890 --> 01:19:56.700
IF THE SEXES WERE SWITCHED,
AND ONLY FEMALE BENEFICIARIES,

01:19:56.700 --> 01:19:59.530
WHERE WE'RE REQUIRED TO
ESTABLISH ACTUAL FINANCIAL

01:19:59.530 --> 01:20:02.350
DEPENDENCY, ONE JUSTICE
WONDERED WOULD THAT MAKE A

01:20:02.350 --> 01:20:04.280
CONSTITUTIONAL DIFFERENCE?

01:20:04.280 --> 01:20:07.690
GINSBURG'S RESPONSE
WAS THE LINE DRAWN HERE

01:20:07.690 --> 01:20:10.980
LIKE VIRTUALLY EVERY GENDER
DISCRIMINATION IS A TWO EDGE

01:20:10.980 --> 01:20:11.980
SWORD.

01:20:11.980 --> 01:20:13.870
HER INTERLOCUTOR PERSISTED.

01:20:13.870 --> 01:20:16.150
SOME RECENT COURT
DECISIONS HAD FOCUSED ON

01:20:16.150 --> 01:20:18.620
THE HISTORY OF
DISCRIMINATION AGAINST WOMEN,

01:20:18.620 --> 01:20:20.990
BUT HE DOUBTED THAT
ANY ANALOGOUS HISTORY

01:20:20.990 --> 01:20:23.650
OF DISCRIMINATION
AGAINST MEN EXISTED.

01:20:23.650 --> 01:20:27.860
GINS BURG RESPONDED THAT MOST
ANTI-FEMALE DISCRIMINATION

01:20:27.860 --> 01:20:31.340
WAS DRESSED UP AS DISCRIMINATION
FAVORING THE WOMEN.

01:20:31.340 --> 01:20:34.570
THE JUSTICE REPLIED
IMPATIENTLY, I KNOW THAT.

01:20:34.570 --> 01:20:36.620
I KNOW THAT BUT
THE COURTS THROUGH

01:20:36.620 --> 01:20:39.860
HELP OF ADVOCATES SUCH AS
YOU HAVE BEEN ABLE TO SEE

01:20:39.860 --> 01:20:41.570
THAT, HAVENT THEY?

01:20:41.570 --> 01:20:44.490
THAT COMMENT ELICITED
LAUGHTER IN THE COURTROOM.

01:20:44.490 --> 01:20:46.870
GINS BURG GAMELY
REITERATED THAT SEX

01:20:46.870 --> 01:20:50.370
CLASSIFICATIONS ALMOST
INEVITABLEY HARMED WOMEN.

01:20:50.370 --> 01:20:52.330
PERSISTING THIS
JUSTICE ASKED HER

01:20:52.330 --> 01:20:56.010
TO IMAGINE AN INSTANCE OF
DISCRIMINATION AGAINST MALES.

01:20:56.010 --> 01:20:59.590
WOULD HER CONSTITUTIONAL
ARGUMENT BE EQUALLY STRONG?

01:20:59.590 --> 01:21:03.080
GINSBURG REPLIED THAT HER
ARGUMENT WOULD REMAIN UNCHANGED

01:21:03.080 --> 01:21:06.220
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
OF ANY PURELY ANTI-MALE

01:21:06.220 --> 01:21:07.380
DISCRIMINATION.

01:21:07.380 --> 01:21:10.540
IN THE END, THE WOMEN ARE
THE ONES WHO END UP HURTING.

01:21:10.540 --> 01:21:13.420
IN A MOMENT LATER,
ANOTHER OF THE JUSTICES

01:21:13.420 --> 01:21:15.770
TOOK UP THE SAME
LINE OF QUESTIONING.

01:21:15.770 --> 01:21:17.700
SHOULD DISCRIMINATION
AGAINST MALES

01:21:17.700 --> 01:21:20.870
BE SUBJECTED TO THE SAME
STANDARD AS DISCRIMINATION

01:21:20.870 --> 01:21:24.080
AGAINST FEMALES OR
TO A DIFFERENT ONE?

01:21:24.080 --> 01:21:26.700
GINSBURG REPEATED
HER PREVIOUS ANSWER.

01:21:26.700 --> 01:21:29.520
ALMOST EVERY DISCRIMINATION
THAT OPERATES AGAINST

01:21:29.520 --> 01:21:33.250
MALES OPERATES AGAINST
FEMALES, AS WELL.

01:21:33.250 --> 01:21:37.010
BEWILDERED AND APPARENTLY
ANNOYED, THE JUSTICE RESPONDED

01:21:37.010 --> 01:21:39.940
IS THAT A YES OR A NO ANSWER?

01:21:39.940 --> 01:21:41.620
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND YOU.

01:21:41.620 --> 01:21:44.230
ARE YOU TRYING TO
AVOID THE QUESTION?

01:21:44.230 --> 01:21:48.340
GINSBURG INSISTED SHE WAS
TRYING TO CLARIFY, NOT EVADE.

01:21:48.340 --> 01:21:50.880
SHE WAS AWARE OF NO SEX
CLASSIFICATIONS THAT DID

01:21:50.880 --> 01:21:53.750
NOT OPERATE AS A
DOUBLE EDGED SWORD.

01:21:53.750 --> 01:21:55.810
THE EXCHANGE WENT
ON TO SIMLAR EFFECT

01:21:55.810 --> 01:21:58.860
FOR A WHILE LONGER THEN CAME
THE FOLLOWING QUESTION FROM THE

01:21:58.860 --> 01:21:59.560
BENCH.

01:21:59.560 --> 01:22:02.580
BUT YOUR ANSWER ALWAYS
DEPENDS ON THERE FINDING SOME

01:22:02.580 --> 01:22:04.790
DISCRIMINATION AGAINST FEMALES.

01:22:04.790 --> 01:22:08.600
YOU SEEM TO PUT THAT IN EVERY
ANSWER TO THIS QUESTION.

01:22:08.600 --> 01:22:11.220
YES.

01:22:11.220 --> 01:22:12.800
GINSBURG WHO MUST
HAVE BEEN GROWING

01:22:12.800 --> 01:22:15.730
EXASPERATED AT THIS POINT
REITERATED THAT QUOTE.

01:22:15.730 --> 01:22:19.370
I HAVE NOT YET COME ACROSS A
STATUTE THAT DOESN'T HAVE THAT

01:22:19.370 --> 01:22:20.250
AFFECT.

01:22:20.250 --> 01:22:21.730
HER QUESTIONER PERSISTED.

01:22:21.730 --> 01:22:23.180
I'M NOT MAKING THIS UP.

01:22:23.180 --> 01:22:26.210
BUT IF THERE WERE ONE, THEN
WOULD YOU SAY IT WOULD BE

01:22:26.210 --> 01:22:29.280
TREATED UNDER A DIFFERENT
STANDARD I TAKE IT?

01:22:29.280 --> 01:22:31.910
NOT WISHING TO ALIENATE
A POTENTIAL ALLY,

01:22:31.910 --> 01:22:33.830
OR TO MAKE A CONCESION
THAT COULD HARM HER

01:22:33.830 --> 01:22:36.150
CASE, GINSBURG RELENTED.

01:22:36.150 --> 01:22:38.930
IF THERE WERE SUCH A
STATUTE, SHE WOULD RESERVE

01:22:38.930 --> 01:22:41.540
JUDGMENT ON WHAT THE
STANDARD WOULD BE.

01:22:41.540 --> 01:22:47.070
BUT SHE REPEATED SHE HAD YET
TO COME ACROSS SUCH A STATUTE.

01:22:47.070 --> 01:22:49.020
THE JUSTICES WHO
WERE ASKING THESE

01:22:49.020 --> 01:22:51.700
QUESTIONS WERE VERY SMART MEN.

01:22:51.700 --> 01:22:53.520
THEIR INABILITY
TO COMPREHEND WHAT

01:22:53.520 --> 01:22:57.160
WOULD STRIKE MOST OF US TODAY
AS A FAIRLY SELF EVIDENT POINT

01:22:57.160 --> 01:23:00.450
SPEAKS VOLUMES ABOUT THE
CHALLENGES THAT SOCIAL REFORM

01:23:00.450 --> 01:23:04.380
LAWYERS FACE IN CONFRONTING
THE DEEPLY ROOTED IDEOLOGIES

01:23:04.380 --> 01:23:08.461
THAT MAKE A SYSTEM OF OPPRESSION
SEEM JUST AND NATURAL.

01:23:08.461 --> 01:23:10.960
I'VE BEEN TALKING ABOUT SOME
OF THE CHALLENGES THAT GINSBURG

01:23:10.960 --> 01:23:14.630
FACED IN COURT OF CONVINCING
MALE JUSTICES AS WHY SEX

01:23:14.630 --> 01:23:17.870
CLASSIFICATIONS WERE HARMFUL TO
WOMEN AND AS SHE WOULD WANT ME

01:23:17.870 --> 01:23:19.500
TO ADD TO MEN AS WELL.

01:23:19.500 --> 01:23:22.030
BUT NOW I WANT TO TURN TO
ANOTHER ASPECT OF THE JOB

01:23:22.030 --> 01:23:23.990
OF SOCIAL REFORM LITIGATORS.

01:23:23.990 --> 01:23:26.220
WE TEND TO THINK OF
LAWYERS AS PEOPLE

01:23:26.220 --> 01:23:29.500
WHO GO INTO COURT IN
PURSUANCE OF A LEGAL CLAIM.

01:23:29.500 --> 01:23:31.920
BUT IN SOME WAYS THE
MOST IMPORTANT JOB

01:23:31.920 --> 01:23:34.690
OF THE SOCIAL REFORM
LITIGATOR DOES NOT TAKE

01:23:34.690 --> 01:23:36.580
PLACE IN THE COURTROOM AT ALL.

01:23:36.580 --> 01:23:38.720
THE STRATEGY OF THE
WOMEN'S RIGHTS PROJECT,

01:23:38.720 --> 01:23:43.190
WHICH GINSBURG HEAD IN THE 1970S
INCLUDED NOT JUST LITIGATING

01:23:43.190 --> 01:23:46.870
CASES, BUT ALSO LOBBYING
LEGISLATURES, TRAINING LAWYERS,

01:23:46.870 --> 01:23:49.120
AND EDUCATING THE
GENERAL PUBLIC ABOUT

01:23:49.120 --> 01:23:51.760
ISSUES OF SEX DISCRIMINATION.

01:23:51.760 --> 01:23:56.400
GINSBURG AND THE WRP OFFERED
ASSISTANCE TO ACLU AFFILIATES

01:23:56.400 --> 01:23:58.470
THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY
WHO WERE ENGAGING

01:23:58.470 --> 01:24:00.600
IN SEX DISCRIMINATION
LITIGATTION.

01:24:00.600 --> 01:24:04.080
SHE ADVISED THEM ON
PRIORITIES AND THE WRP SERVED

01:24:04.080 --> 01:24:06.370
AS A CLEARINGHOUSE
FOR INFORMATION,

01:24:06.370 --> 01:24:09.780
BOTH ABOUT PENDING SEX
DISCRIMINATION CASES AND ABOUT

01:24:09.780 --> 01:24:12.250
LAWYERS WHO WERE WILLING
TO HELP OUT WITH THEM.

01:24:12.250 --> 01:24:15.110
AFTER HER LEGAL VICTORIES,
GINSBURG WOULD WRITE MEMOS

01:24:15.110 --> 01:24:17.840
TO ACLU AFFILIATES
INSTRUCTING THEM ON HOW

01:24:17.840 --> 01:24:21.380
TO PURSUE FOLLOW UP LITIGATION
AND LEGISLATIVE LOBBYING.

01:24:21.380 --> 01:24:23.220
GINSBURG DEVOTED
AT LEAST AS MUCH

01:24:23.220 --> 01:24:27.090
OF HER TIME TO EDUCATING PEOPLE
ABOUT SEX DISCRIMINATION AS SHE

01:24:27.090 --> 01:24:30.320
DID LITIGATING SEX
EQUALITY CASES.

01:24:30.320 --> 01:24:32.150
WHEN HER FEMALE
STUDENTS AT RUTGERS

01:24:32.150 --> 01:24:36.100
LAW SCHOOL IN THE 1960S
ASKED FOR A SEMINAR ON WOMEN

01:24:36.100 --> 01:24:39.590
AND THE LAW, GINSBURG SPENT A
MONTH IN THE LIBRARY READING

01:24:39.590 --> 01:24:42.410
EVERY COURT DECISION
AND LAW REVIEW ARTICLE

01:24:42.410 --> 01:24:45.660
ON THE SUBJECT SHE
COULD FIND, WHICH

01:24:45.660 --> 01:24:48.040
SHE REPORTS WAS NOT A
VERY TAXING ENDEAVOR,

01:24:48.040 --> 01:24:50.230
GIVEN HOW LITTLE THERE WAS.

01:24:50.230 --> 01:24:52.730
THEN SHE INITIATED
SUCH A COURSE AND WITH

01:24:52.730 --> 01:24:55.200
TWO OF HER COLLEAGUES SHE PUT
TOGETHER ONE OF THE NATION'S

01:24:55.200 --> 01:24:58.010
FIRST CASE BOOKS ON
WOMEN AND THE LAW.

01:24:58.010 --> 01:25:00.830
SHE ALSO WROTE NUMEROUS
LAW REVIEW ARTICLES

01:25:00.830 --> 01:25:02.820
ON SEX DISCRIMINATION
LITIGATION,

01:25:02.820 --> 01:25:05.500
AND SHE MAINTAINED A STEADY
STREAM OF CORRESPONDENCE,

01:25:05.500 --> 01:25:08.470
WHICH STUDENT LAW REVIEW
EDITORS, URGING THEM TO WRITE

01:25:08.470 --> 01:25:11.830
ABOUT RACE AND SEX
DISCRIMINATION CASES, EDUCATING

01:25:11.830 --> 01:25:14.940
THEM ABOUT THE ISSUES, AND
PROVIDING THEM WITH BRIEFS

01:25:14.940 --> 01:25:17.890
AND OTHER MATERIALS TO
ENHANCE THEIR SCHOLARSHIP.

01:25:17.890 --> 01:25:21.200
AND SHE TRAVELED AROUND THE
COUNTRY TESTIFYING BEFORE

01:25:21.200 --> 01:25:24.120
LEGISLATURES IN SUPPORT OF
THE EQUAL RIGHTS AMENDMENT

01:25:24.120 --> 01:25:28.440
AND SPEAKING TO ACLU AFFILIATES
AND UNIVERSITY AUDIENCES ABOUT

01:25:28.440 --> 01:25:30.300
ISSUES OF SEX EQUALITY.

01:25:30.300 --> 01:25:33.750
SHE WAS AN ORGANIZER, A
MOBILIZER, A PUBLICIST

01:25:33.750 --> 01:25:36.600
AND AN EDUCATOR FOR THE
SEX EQUALITY MOVEMENT,

01:25:36.600 --> 01:25:39.070
MUCH AS THURGOOD MARSHALL
HAD BEEN FOR THE CIVIL RIGHTS

01:25:39.070 --> 01:25:41.560
MOVEMENT A GENERATION EARLIER.

01:25:41.560 --> 01:25:44.850
WHLE DOING ALL THESE THINGS THE
SOCIAL REFORM LITIGATOR ALSO

01:25:44.850 --> 01:25:48.540
HAS TO FACE THE DAY TO DAY
CHALLENGES POSED BY AN UNJUST

01:25:48.540 --> 01:25:51.380
STATUS QUO THAT THEY'RE
LITIGATING AGAINST.

01:25:51.380 --> 01:25:53.630
WHEN ARGUING RACE
DISCRIMINATION CASES

01:25:53.630 --> 01:25:57.180
IN THE SUPREME COURT
IN THE 1930S AND 1940S,

01:25:57.180 --> 01:26:00.360
THURGOOD MARSHALL HAD A HARD
TIME FINDING A RESTAURANT TO

01:26:00.360 --> 01:26:02.490
EAT AT IN THE
THOROUGHLY SEGREGATED

01:26:02.490 --> 01:26:04.220
DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA.

01:26:04.220 --> 01:26:06.860
GINS BURG FACED A SIMILAR
CHALLENGE AS CAPTURED

01:26:06.860 --> 01:26:09.520
IN A STORY SHE TELLS
FROM THIS TIME PERIOD.

01:26:09.520 --> 01:26:12.030
NOW REMEMBER, SHE'S A TENURED
PROFESSOR AT COLUMBIA LAW

01:26:12.030 --> 01:26:13.930
SCHOOL, SHE'S HEAD
OF THE WOMEN'S RIGHTS

01:26:13.930 --> 01:26:16.110
PROJECT, SHE'S A
SUPREME COURT LITIGATOR

01:26:16.110 --> 01:26:19.710
AND A FREQUENT WITNESS ACRSS THE
COUNTRY ON BEHALF OF THE ERA.

01:26:19.710 --> 01:26:22.750
BUT SHE'S ALSO RECEIVING
REPEATED PHONE CALLS AT HER

01:26:22.750 --> 01:26:25.900
OFFICE ABOUT HER SON JAMES
WHO IS THEN TEN YEARS

01:26:25.900 --> 01:26:29.350
OLD WHO IS ACTING UP AT SCHOOL
IN THE WAY 10 YEAR OLDS ARE

01:26:29.350 --> 01:26:30.690
WANT TO DO.

01:26:30.690 --> 01:26:34.090
FINALY EXASPERATED AT THE
REPEATED PHONE CALLS GINSBURG

01:26:34.090 --> 01:26:36.880
RESPONDED TO ONE
OF THEM AS FOLLOWS.

01:26:36.880 --> 01:26:39.400
THIS CHILD HAS TWO PARENTS.

01:26:39.400 --> 01:26:42.150
I SUGGEST FROM NOW ON
YOU ALTERNATE BETWEEN

01:26:42.150 --> 01:26:45.130
THEM WHEN YOU NEED TO SPEAK
TO SOMEONE ABOUT JAMES.

01:26:45.130 --> 01:26:48.122
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

01:26:55.060 --> 01:26:58.360
GINSBURG REPORTS THAT EVEN
THOUGH JAMES' BEHAVIOR DID NOT

01:26:58.360 --> 01:27:01.190
MATERIALLY IMPROVE,
THE PHONE CALL CEASED

01:27:01.190 --> 01:27:02.760
BECAUSE THE SCHOOL
WOULD NOT DREAM

01:27:02.760 --> 01:27:08.940
OF BOTHERING A BUSY MALE TAX
ATTORNEY AT HIS OFFICE DURING

01:27:08.940 --> 01:27:10.490
WORKING HOURS.

01:27:10.490 --> 01:27:13.560
SOCIAL REFORM LAWYERS NOT
ONLY MOBILIZED PROTESTS,

01:27:13.560 --> 01:27:15.700
THEY ALSO PROVIDE,
I'M ALMOST DONE,

01:27:15.700 --> 01:27:19.490
VALUABLE ROLE MODELS FOR MEMBERS
OF TRADITIONALLY SUBORDINATED

01:27:19.490 --> 01:27:20.220
GROUPS.

01:27:20.220 --> 01:27:22.960
IN 1960 OF COURSE, THERE
HAD NEVER BEEN A WOMAN

01:27:22.960 --> 01:27:24.710
ON THE UNITED STATES
SUPREME COURT.

01:27:24.710 --> 01:27:27.720
THERE HAD BEEN ONLY TWO
OR THREE FEDERAL FEMALE

01:27:27.720 --> 01:27:30.020
JUDGES IN THE HISTORY
OF THE COUNTRY.

01:27:30.020 --> 01:27:33.230
IN THE LATE 1940S, PRESIDENT
HARRY TRUMAN APPARENTLY BRIEFLY

01:27:33.230 --> 01:27:36.390
CONSIDERED APPOINTING A WOMAN
TO THE SUPREME COURT, FLORENCE

01:27:36.390 --> 01:27:39.770
ALAN, WHO WAS SITTING ON THE 6TH
CIRCUIT COURT OF APPEALS, BUT

01:27:39.770 --> 01:27:42.090
WHEN HE CONSULTED WITH
THE SITTING JUSTICES,

01:27:42.090 --> 01:27:45.760
APPARENTLY THAT WAS A MISTAKE,
THEY URGED AGAINST DOING SO,

01:27:45.760 --> 01:27:48.790
APPARENTLY THEIR CONCERN WAS
THAT HER PRESENCE WOULD INHIBIT

01:27:48.790 --> 01:27:52.520
THEM FROM TAKING OFF THEIR TIES
AND KICKING UP THEIR FEET AT

01:27:52.520 --> 01:27:53.450
CONFERENCE.

01:27:53.450 --> 01:27:55.850
IN THE MID 1960S,
WOMEN WERE ONLY

01:27:55.850 --> 01:27:58.450
ABOUT 1% OF SUPREME
COURT LITIGATORS.

01:27:58.450 --> 01:28:01.480
LESS THAN 2% OF THE
NATION'S LAW PROFESSORS.

01:28:01.480 --> 01:28:04.720
JUSTICE GINSBURG DID NOT HAVE A
SINGLE FEMALE PROFESSOR DURING

01:28:04.720 --> 01:28:06.470
HER THREE YEARS OF LAW SCHOOL.

01:28:06.470 --> 01:28:09.620
NOT UNTIL 1970, IF
YOU CAN BELIEVE THIS,

01:28:09.620 --> 01:28:12.680
DID THE AMERICAN ASSOCIATION
OF LAW SCHOOLS AMMEND ITS RULES

01:28:12.680 --> 01:28:15.900
TO BAR SEX DISCRIMINATION
AT MEMBER INSTITUTIONS

01:28:15.900 --> 01:28:18.390
AND AS OF THAT YEAR
WOMEN WERE ONLY

01:28:18.390 --> 01:28:21.840
ABOUT 10% OF LAW
SCHOOL STUDENT BODIES.

01:28:21.840 --> 01:28:23.600
GINSBURG APPRECIATED
THE IMPORTANCE

01:28:23.600 --> 01:28:26.970
OF FEMALE LAWYERS PARTICIPATING
IN SEX EQUALITY CASES.

01:28:26.970 --> 01:28:30.630
WHEN SHE LEARNED OF THE ACLU'S
INVOLVEMENT AND WHAT TURNED OUT

01:28:30.630 --> 01:28:33.010
TO BE THE SUPREME COURT'S
LANDMARK SEX EQUALITY

01:28:33.010 --> 01:28:35.370
DECISION IN 1971.

01:28:35.370 --> 01:28:38.150
SHE ASKED THE ORGANIZATION'S
LEGAL DIRECTOR WHETHER

01:28:38.150 --> 01:28:41.510
A WOMAN OUGHT NOT TO BE INVOLVED
AS CO-COUNCIL IN THE CASE.

01:28:41.510 --> 01:28:44.130
HE AGREED AND OFFERED
HER TO JOIN HIM.

01:28:44.130 --> 01:28:48.970
IN WRP LITIGATION WOMEN'S RIGHTS
PROJECTS LITIGATION GINSBURG

01:28:48.970 --> 01:28:51.320
LATER NOTED,
PARTICULAR ATTENTION

01:28:51.320 --> 01:28:54.320
WAS GIVEN TO ENCOURAGING
PARTICIPATION BY WOMEN LAWYERS

01:28:54.320 --> 01:28:57.210
WHO SEEK ASSISTANCE IN
MAINTAINING THEIR SKILLS DURING

01:28:57.210 --> 01:28:59.720
PERIODS WHEN FAMILY
RESPONSIBILITIES PREVENT

01:28:59.720 --> 01:29:02.100
THEM FROM WORKING FULL TIME.

01:29:02.100 --> 01:29:04.940
GINSBURG'S LEADERSHIP
OF THE WRP AND HER ORAL

01:29:04.940 --> 01:29:07.410
ADVOCACY IN THE UNITED
STATES SUPREME COURT WERE

01:29:07.410 --> 01:29:09.940
INSPIRATIONAL TO
COUNTLESS WOMEN.

01:29:09.940 --> 01:29:12.170
SHE HERSELF NEVER FAILED
TO HIGHLIGHT THE COUNTLESS

01:29:12.170 --> 01:29:15.410
CONTRIBUTIONS OF PAST
GENERATIONS OF FEMINISTS TO HER

01:29:15.410 --> 01:29:16.250
OWN WORK.

01:29:16.250 --> 01:29:19.070
IN HER BRIEF IN THE COURT'S
LANDMARK SEX DISCRIMINATION

01:29:19.070 --> 01:29:22.840
CASE, SHE PLACED THE NAMES OF
TRAILBLAZING FEMINISTS DOROTHY

01:29:22.840 --> 01:29:25.510
KENYON AND PAULI MURRAY
ON THE TITLE PAGE

01:29:25.510 --> 01:29:29.230
AS A SYMBOLIC ACKNOWLEDGMENT OF
THE INTELLECTUAL DEBT OWED TO

01:29:29.230 --> 01:29:31.510
THEM BY CONTEMPORARY FEMINISTS.

01:29:31.510 --> 01:29:34.020
AND LATER AS A SUPREME COURT
JUSTICE SHE WROTE NUMEROUS

01:29:34.020 --> 01:29:36.260
ARTICLES DESCRIBING
THE CONTRIBUTION

01:29:36.260 --> 01:29:39.420
OF PIONEERING FEMINIST
LAWYERS AND JUDGES, AS WELL

01:29:39.420 --> 01:29:42.160
AS THE WIVES OF
SUPREME COURT JUSTICES.

01:29:42.160 --> 01:29:45.180
MANY SOCIAL REFORM
ACTIVISTS DO NOT LIVE TO

01:29:45.180 --> 01:29:47.960
SEE THE DAY THAT THEIR
DREAMS ARE REALIZED.

01:29:47.960 --> 01:29:51.780
MANY OF THE FIRST GENERATION OF
ABOLITIONISTS DID NOT SURVIVE

01:29:51.780 --> 01:29:55.010
TO SEE THE ENACTMENT OF THE 13TH
AMENDMENT ENDING OF SLAVERY.

01:29:55.010 --> 01:29:58.530
AND SUSAN B. ANTHONY AND
ELIZABETH CADY STANTON DID NOT

01:29:58.530 --> 01:30:01.960
LIVE TO SEE THE ENACTMENT OF
THE 19TH AMENDMENT ENFRANCHISING

01:30:01.960 --> 01:30:02.750
WOMEN.

01:30:02.750 --> 01:30:05.160
JUSTICE GINSBURG, OF
COURSE, HAS NOT ONLY LIVED

01:30:05.160 --> 01:30:07.870
TO SEE THE ENORMOUS
CHANGES IN SEX EQUALITY,

01:30:07.870 --> 01:30:11.250
BUT HAS HELPED TO BRING THEM
ABOUT AS A SUPREME COURT

01:30:11.250 --> 01:30:15.910
JUSTICE AS IN HER LANDMARK
DECISION 20 YEARS AGO REQUIRING

01:30:15.910 --> 01:30:19.320
VIRGINIA MILITARY
INSTITUTE TO ADMIT WOMEN.

01:30:19.320 --> 01:30:22.220
JUSTICE GINSBURG, WE'RE SO
HAPPY YOU'VE AFFORDED US THIS

01:30:22.220 --> 01:30:23.490
OCCASION TODAY.

01:30:23.490 --> 01:30:26.290
IN CELEBRATING YOUR
EXTRAORDINARY CONTRIBUTIONS

01:30:26.290 --> 01:30:29.140
BOTH TO SEX EQUALITY AND
MORE GENERALLY MAKING

01:30:29.140 --> 01:30:31.230
OURS A MORE JUST SOCIETY.

01:30:31.230 --> 01:30:33.350
WE'RE ALL IN YOUR DEBT.

01:30:33.350 --> 01:31:20.620
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

01:31:20.620 --> 01:31:21.120
[APPLAUSE]

01:31:21.120 --> 01:31:22.820
&gt;&gt; THANK YOU SO MUCH MICHAEL.

01:31:22.820 --> 01:31:25.010
AND DID I TELL YOU THAT
WAS THE VERY BEST JOB

01:31:25.010 --> 01:31:27.120
TO HAVE IN THE WORLD.

01:31:27.120 --> 01:31:28.940
LIZ, ARE YOU GOING TO
THANK OUR PANELISTS?

01:31:28.940 --> 01:31:30.890
&gt;&gt; TWO THINGS I'M GOING TO SAY.

01:31:30.890 --> 01:31:33.440
&gt;&gt; ARE YOU GOING TO THANK THEM?

01:31:33.440 --> 01:31:34.980
&gt;&gt; I AM.

01:31:34.980 --> 01:31:35.480
AND YOU!

01:31:35.480 --> 01:31:39.050
I WILL JUST TIE THINGS
UP HERE QUICKLY.

01:31:39.050 --> 01:31:42.790
I WANT TO THANK MARGIE
AND THE PANELISTS.

01:31:42.790 --> 01:31:46.300
YOU'VE TAUGHT US A GREAT DEAL
ABOUT THE FIRST DECADE OF THE

01:31:46.300 --> 01:31:47.420
ROBERTS COURT.

01:31:47.420 --> 01:31:53.680
AND I THINK YOU
HAVE EQUIPPED US,

01:31:53.680 --> 01:31:59.150
YOU HAVE EQUIPPED US WELL FOR
A FUTURE OF COURT WATCHING.

01:31:59.150 --> 01:32:02.500
I WANT TO THANK THE AUDIENCE
FOR JOINING US THIS MORNING.

01:32:02.500 --> 01:32:04.850
IN CAMBRIDGE AND
THE MANY PEOPLE WHO

01:32:04.850 --> 01:32:08.360
ARE ONLINE TO HONOR JUSTICE
RUTH BADER GINSBURG.

01:32:08.360 --> 01:32:09.910
[MUSIC]

